// German v2 Unit 22 — Arabic source language (srcLang:"ar")
// Auto-generated. Fields marked [AR] need manual Arabic translation.
const UNIT_22_AR = {n:22,lang:"de",srcLang:"ar",track:"v2",title:"Umwelt und Alltag",sub:"Environment, sustainability, Partizip I+II as adjectives, lassen causative",icon:"♻️",level:"B1.2",color:"#7B5EE8",lessons:[
    {id:"deu_r22l1",title:"Nachhaltigkeit im Büro",icon:"♻️",xp:15,board:true,steps:[
        {type:"intro",title:"Nachhaltigkeit im Büro",desc:"[AR] Verumius stands before his colleagues and gives a presentation. In German. His topic: sustainability in the office. Time to learn the most important environmental words.",goals:[
            "[AR] Learn 18 key vocabulary words related to the environment and climate",
            "[AR] Follow Verumius through his first presentation in German",
            "[AR] Understand trends and statistics on the topic of sustainability"
          ]},
        {type:"story",speaker:"narrator",mood:"proud",art:"de-office-presentation",trg:"Ein Jahr in Berlin. Verumius steht vor seinen Kollegen und hält eine Präsentation. Auf Deutsch. Mia sitzt in der zweiten Reihe und nickt ermutigend. Sein Thema: Nachhaltigkeit im Büro.",src:"[AR] One year in Berlin. Verumius stands before his colleagues and gives a presentation. In German. Mia sits in the second row, nodding encouragingly. His topic: sustainability in the office."},
        {type:"teach",trg:"die Umwelt",src:"[AR] the environment",pos:"noun",gender:"f",note:"[AR] Um (around) + Welt (world). Everything that surrounds you.\nGermans rank environmental protection as a top political priority.",example:"A: Was ist dir wichtig?\nB: Die Umwelt ist mir sehr wichtig.\nA: Was tust du für die Umwelt?\nB: Ich trenne meinen Müll und spare Strom.",exampleSrc:"[AR] A: What is important to you?\nB: The environment is very important to me.\nA: What do you do for the environment?\nB: I separate my trash and save electricity.",funFact:"[AR] Um (around) + Welt (world). The world around you. Germans rank environmental protection as a top political priority. The Umwelt is not just nature. It is everything that surrounds you."},
        {type:"teach",trg:"der Umweltschutz",src:"[AR] environmental protection",pos:"noun",gender:"m",note:"[AR] Umwelt + Schutz (protection). Germany pioneered the Green Party in 1980.\nEmbedded in Article 20a of the German constitution.",example:"A: Was bedeutet Umweltschutz für dich?\nB: Weniger Plastik, mehr Recycling.\nA: Ist Umweltschutz in Deutschland wichtig?\nB: Ja, es steht sogar im Grundgesetz.",exampleSrc:"[AR] A: What does environmental protection mean to you?\nB: Less plastic, more recycling.\nA: Is environmental protection important in Germany?\nB: Yes, it is even in the constitution.",funFact:"[AR] Umwelt + Schutz (protection). Germany pioneered the Green Party (Die Grünen) in 1980. Umweltschutz is embedded in Article 20a of the German constitution."},
        {type:"teach",trg:"die Energie",src:"[AR] energy",pos:"noun",gender:"f",note:"[AR] From Greek 'energeia' (activity). The Energiewende aims to\nphase out nuclear and fossil fuels in Germany.",example:"A: Woher kommt unsere Energie?\nB: Immer mehr aus Wind und Sonne.\nA: Und der Rest?\nB: Noch aus Kohle und Gas, leider.",exampleSrc:"[AR] A: Where does our energy come from?\nB: More and more from wind and sun.\nA: And the rest?\nB: Still from coal and gas, unfortunately.",funFact:"[AR] From Greek 'energeia' (activity). 'Erneuerbare Energie' (renewable energy) is Germany's obsession. The Energiewende (energy transition) aims to phase out nuclear and fossil fuels."},
        {type:"teach",trg:"das Klima",src:"[AR] the climate",pos:"noun",gender:"n",note:"[AR] From Greek 'klima' (inclination/region). Neuter.\n'Klimawandel' (climate change) dominates German news.",example:"A: Wie ist das Klima in Deutschland?\nB: Mild, aber es ändert sich.\nA: Der Klimawandel?\nB: Ja, die Sommer werden heißer.",exampleSrc:"[AR] A: What is the climate like in Germany?\nB: Mild, but it is changing.\nA: Climate change?\nB: Yes, the summers are getting hotter.",funFact:"[AR] From Greek 'klima' (inclination/region). 'Klimawandel' (climate change) and 'Klimaschutz' (climate protection) dominate German news. 'Klimaneutral' is the target."},
        {type:"teach",trg:"der Strom",src:"[AR] electricity",pos:"noun",gender:"m",note:"[AR] Also means 'stream' or 'current.' From the flowing motion.\n'Ökostrom' (green electricity) is a real product you can buy.",example:"A: Wie viel Strom verbrauchen wir?\nB: Zu viel. Wir müssen sparen.\nA: Haben wir Ökostrom?\nB: Ja, seit letztem Jahr.",exampleSrc:"[AR] A: How much electricity do we use?\nB: Too much. We need to save.\nA: Do we have green electricity?\nB: Yes, since last year.",funFact:"[AR] 'Electricity' AND 'stream/current.' From the flowing motion of electric current. 'Ökostrom' (green electricity) is a real product you can buy. 'Der Strom fließt' works for rivers and wires."},
        {type:"teach",trg:"die Luft",src:"[AR] the air",pos:"noun",gender:"f",note:"[AR] Cognate with English 'loft' (high air). 'Frische Luft' is\na German prescription for everything.",example:"A: Die Luft hier ist nicht gut.\nB: Ja, zu viele Autos.\nA: Geh an die frische Luft!\nB: Gute Idee. Ich gehe in den Park.",exampleSrc:"[AR] A: The air here is not good.\nB: Yes, too many cars.\nA: Get some fresh air!\nB: Good idea. I'll go to the park.",funFact:"[AR] Cognate with English 'loft' (high air). 'Frische Luft' (fresh air) is a German prescription for everything. Feeling tired? 'Geh an die frische Luft!' Air quality is a major environmental metric."},
        {type:"teach",trg:"der Boden",src:"[AR] the ground, soil, floor",pos:"noun",gender:"m",note:"[AR] Triple meaning: 'fruchtbarer Boden' (fertile soil),\n'Erdboden' (ground), 'Fußboden' (floor).",example:"A: Der Boden hier ist sehr fruchtbar.\nB: Ja, perfekt für Gemüse.\nA: Und der Fußboden im Büro?\nB: Der muss auch sauber bleiben!",exampleSrc:"[AR] A: The soil here is very fertile.\nB: Yes, perfect for vegetables.\nA: And the floor in the office?\nB: That needs to stay clean too!",funFact:"[AR] Triple meaning. 'Fruchtbarer Boden' (fertile soil), 'Erdboden' (ground), 'Fußboden' (floor). Related to English 'bottom.' The foundation of everything."},
        {type:"teach",trg:"die Erde",src:"[AR] the earth, soil",pos:"noun",gender:"f",note:"[AR] Both the planet and the dirt. Cognate with English 'earth.'\n'Die Erde dreht sich' (the earth turns).",example:"A: Die Erde ist unser einziger Planet.\nB: Deshalb müssen wir sie schützen.\nA: Was liegt in der Erde?\nB: Samen, Wurzeln und Mineralien.",exampleSrc:"[AR] A: The earth is our only planet.\nB: That's why we have to protect it.\nA: What is in the soil?\nB: Seeds, roots, and minerals.",funFact:"[AR] Both the planet and the dirt. Cognate with English 'earth.' 'Die Erde dreht sich' (the earth turns). 'In der Erde' (in the soil). Like English, one word for planet and ground."},
        {type:"teach",trg:"die Temperatur",src:"[AR] the temperature",pos:"noun",gender:"f",note:"[AR] From Latin 'temperatura.' Germany uses Celsius.\n30+ degrees is a heatwave. Most homes have no AC.",example:"A: Wie ist die Temperatur heute?\nB: 35 Grad! Viel zu heiß.\nA: Das ist extrem für Deutschland.\nB: Ja, früher war das selten.",exampleSrc:"[AR] A: What is the temperature today?\nB: 35 degrees! Way too hot.\nA: That is extreme for Germany.\nB: Yes, it used to be rare.",funFact:"[AR] From Latin 'temperatura.' Germany uses Celsius. 0 degrees is freezing, 20 is comfortable, 30+ is a heatwave. Germans panic at 35 degrees because most homes have no air conditioning."},
        {type:"teach",trg:"die Hitze",src:"[AR] the heat",pos:"noun",gender:"f",note:"[AR] From 'heiß' (hot). 'Hitzewelle' (heatwave).\nGermany's record: 42.6 degrees Celsius in 2019.",example:"A: Diese Hitze ist unerträglich!\nB: Ja, 40 Grad im Schatten.\nA: Hast du eine Klimaanlage?\nB: Nein, die braucht man hier normalerweise nicht.",exampleSrc:"[AR] A: This heat is unbearable!\nB: Yes, 40 degrees in the shade.\nA: Do you have air conditioning?\nB: No, you normally don't need it here.",funFact:"[AR] From 'heiß' (hot). 'Hitzewelle' (heatwave). Germany's record: 42.6 degrees Celsius in 2019. 'Vor Hitze umkommen' (to perish from heat) is how Germans describe summer."},
        {type:"teach",trg:"die Kontrolle",src:"[AR] the control, check, inspection",pos:"noun",gender:"f",note:"[AR] From French 'contrôle.' 'Qualitätskontrolle' (quality control),\n'Passkontrolle' (passport check).",example:"A: Wir brauchen mehr Kontrolle.\nB: Über den Energieverbrauch?\nA: Ja, und über die Abgase.\nB: Kontrolle ist der erste Schritt.",exampleSrc:"[AR] A: We need more control.\nB: Over energy consumption?\nA: Yes, and over exhaust fumes.\nB: Control is the first step.",funFact:"[AR] From French 'contrôle.' 'Qualitätskontrolle' (quality control), 'Passkontrolle' (passport check). Germans love Kontrolle in all forms. Ordnung muss sein."},
        {type:"teach",trg:"das System",src:"[AR] the system",pos:"noun",gender:"n",note:"[AR] From Greek 'systema.' Neuter. 'Das Pfandsystem' is world-famous.\nGermany recycles 70%+ of packaging.",example:"A: Das Pfandsystem funktioniert gut.\nB: Ja, Deutschland recycelt fast alles.\nA: Brauchen wir ein besseres System?\nB: Für Plastik ja, definitiv.",exampleSrc:"[AR] A: The deposit system works well.\nB: Yes, Germany recycles almost everything.\nA: Do we need a better system?\nB: For plastic, yes, definitely.",funFact:"[AR] From Greek 'systema.' 'Das Pfandsystem' (deposit system) is world-famous. Germany recycles 70%+ of packaging. The system works because it is a System."},
        {type:"teach",trg:"die Statistik",src:"[AR] statistics",pos:"noun",gender:"f",note:"[AR] From Latin 'statisticum' (of the state). Originally meant state data.\n'Laut Statistik' (according to statistics).",example:"A: Laut Statistik steigt die Temperatur.\nB: Wie viel pro Jahr?\nA: Im Durchschnitt 0,3 Grad.\nB: Das klingt wenig, ist aber viel.",exampleSrc:"[AR] A: According to statistics, the temperature is rising.\nB: How much per year?\nA: On average 0.3 degrees.\nB: That sounds little, but it is a lot.",funFact:"[AR] From Latin 'statisticum' (of the state). Originally meant state data. 'Laut Statistik' (according to statistics) is how German presentations begin. Germans trust numbers."},
        {type:"teach",trg:"der Durchschnitt",src:"[AR] the average",pos:"noun",gender:"m",note:"[AR] Durch (through) + Schnitt (cut). A cut through the middle.\n'Im Durchschnitt' (on average).",example:"A: Was ist der Durchschnitt?\nB: Im Durchschnitt 20 Grad.\nA: Und dieses Jahr?\nB: Über dem Durchschnitt, leider.",exampleSrc:"[AR] A: What is the average?\nB: On average 20 degrees.\nA: And this year?\nB: Above average, unfortunately.",funFact:"[AR] Durch (through) + Schnitt (cut). A cut through the middle. The average. 'Im Durchschnitt' (on average). Literally slicing through data to find the middle. German compound logic at its finest."},
        {type:"teach",trg:"steigen",src:"[AR] to rise, to climb",pos:"verb",gender:null,note:"[AR] Irregular: stieg, gestiegen. 'Die Temperaturen steigen.'\n'Einsteigen' (to board), 'aussteigen' (to exit).",example:"A: Die Preise steigen wieder.\nB: Ja, und die Temperaturen auch.\nA: Steigt auch der Meeresspiegel?\nB: Leider ja, jedes Jahr.",exampleSrc:"[AR] A: The prices are rising again.\nB: Yes, and the temperatures too.\nA: Is the sea level also rising?\nB: Unfortunately yes, every year.",funFact:"[AR] Irregular: stieg, gestiegen. 'Die Temperaturen steigen' (temperatures are rising). 'Einsteigen' (to board), 'aussteigen' (to exit). A verb of upward motion in every context."},
        {type:"teach",trg:"sinken",src:"[AR] to sink, to fall, to decrease",pos:"verb",gender:null,note:"[AR] Irregular: sank, gesunken. 'Die Kosten sinken.'\nCognate with English 'sink.' The opposite of steigen.",example:"A: Sinkt der Energieverbrauch?\nB: Ja, langsam.\nA: Und die Kosten?\nB: Die sinken leider nicht.",exampleSrc:"[AR] A: Is energy consumption decreasing?\nB: Yes, slowly.\nA: And the costs?\nB: Those are unfortunately not decreasing.",funFact:"[AR] Irregular: sank, gesunken. 'Die Kosten sinken' (costs are falling). Cognate with English 'sink.' The opposite of steigen. These two verbs describe every graph."},
        {type:"teach",trg:"reduzieren",src:"[AR] to reduce",pos:"verb",gender:null,note:"[AR] From Latin 'reducere.' The -ieren ending marks a borrowed verb.\nRegular conjugation. International and professional.",example:"A: Wir müssen den Stromverbrauch reduzieren.\nB: Um wie viel Prozent?\nA: Um mindestens 30 Prozent.\nB: Das ist viel, aber machbar.",exampleSrc:"[AR] A: We need to reduce electricity consumption.\nB: By how many percent?\nA: By at least 30 percent.\nB: That is a lot, but doable.",funFact:"[AR] From Latin 'reducere.' The -ieren ending marks a borrowed verb. 'Emissionen reduzieren' (to reduce emissions). Regular conjugation. International and professional."},
        {type:"teach",trg:"extrem",src:"[AR] extreme, extremely",pos:"adj",gender:null,note:"[AR] From Latin 'extremus.' Functions as both adjective and\nintensifying adverb. 'Extrem wichtig' (extremely important).",example:"A: Das Wetter ist extrem heiß.\nB: Ja, 42 Grad ist extrem.\nA: Ist das normal?\nB: Nein, das ist extrem ungewöhnlich.",exampleSrc:"[AR] A: The weather is extremely hot.\nB: Yes, 42 degrees is extreme.\nA: Is that normal?\nB: No, that is extremely unusual.",funFact:"[AR] From Latin 'extremus.' 'Extreme Hitze' (extreme heat), 'extrem wichtig' (extremely important). Functions as both adjective and intensifying adverb. Germans use it like English 'extremely.'"},
        {type:"story",speaker:"verumius",mood:"nervous",art:"de-office-presentation",trg:"Die steigenden Temperaturen sind ein Problem für alle. Im Durchschnitt verbraucht unser Büro 30 Prozent mehr Strom als nötig. Das können wir reduzieren.",src:"[AR] The rising temperatures are a problem for everyone. On average our office uses 30 percent more electricity than necessary. We can reduce that."},
        {type:"story",speaker:"mia",mood:"proud",art:"de-office-presentation",trg:"Applaus aus der zweiten Reihe. Mia klatscht als Erste. Vor einem Jahr konnte er kaum eine Kaffeebestellung aufgeben. Heute hält er eine Präsentation über Klimaschutz. Auf Deutsch.",src:"[AR] Applause from the second row. Mia claps first. A year ago he could barely place a coffee order. Today he gives a presentation about climate protection. In German."},
        {type:"mc",q:"Verumius hält eine Präsentation über Energie im Büro. Welches Wort bedeutet 'electricity'?",opts:["Stern","Strom","Sturm","Stein"],ans:"Strom",hint:"[AR] This word also means 'stream' or 'current.' It flows through cables."},
        {type:"fb",s:"Die Temperaturen {1} jedes Jahr.",a:["steigen"],opts:["steigen","sinken","reduzieren","kontrollieren"],hint:"[AR] Which verb means 'to rise'? The temperatures go up, not down.",sSrc:"[AR] The temperatures rise every year."},
        {type:"match",pairs:[
            {trg:"Umwelt",src:"environment"},
            {trg:"Klima",src:"climate"},
            {trg:"Energie",src:"energy"},
            {trg:"Durchschnitt",src:"average"}
          ]},
        {type:"story",speaker:"narrator",mood:"satisfied",art:"de-office-presentation",trg:"Stille im Raum. Dann Applaus. Nicht perfekt, nicht fehlerfrei. Aber auf Deutsch. Ein ganzer Vortrag auf Deutsch. Verumius atmet aus. Der erste Schritt ist getan.",src:"[AR] Silence in the room. Then applause. Not perfect, not flawless. But in German. An entire presentation in German. Verumius breathes out. The first step is taken."}
      ]},
    {id:"deu_r22l2",title:"Grün denken",icon:"🌿",xp:15,board:true,steps:[
        {type:"intro",title:"Grün denken",desc:"[AR] Waste separation, recycling, materials, and trade. Today you expand your environmental vocabulary.",goals:[
            "[AR] Learn vocabulary for waste and recycling",
            "[AR] Understand vocabulary for materials and trade",
            "[AR] Build your environmental toolkit"
          ]},
        {type:"story",speaker:"narrator",mood:"observant",art:"de-office-kitchen",trg:"In der Büroküche steht Verumius vor vier verschiedenen Mülleimern. Gelb, blau, braun, schwarz. Vor einem Jahr hätte er alles in einen geworfen. Heute sortiert er automatisch. Lukas schaut zu und schüttelt den Kopf.",src:"[AR] In the office kitchen, Verumius stands in front of four different trash bins. Yellow, blue, brown, black. A year ago he would have thrown everything in one. Today he sorts automatically. Lukas watches and shakes his head."},
        {type:"teach",trg:"der Abfall",src:"[AR] the waste, garbage",pos:"noun",gender:"m",note:"[AR] Ab (off/away) + Fall (fall). Something that falls away.\n'Abfall trennen' (to separate waste) is a German commandment.",example:"A: Wo kommt der Abfall hin?\nB: In die richtige Tonne, natürlich.\nA: Und wenn man den Abfall nicht trennt?\nB: Dann ärgern sich die Nachbarn.",exampleSrc:"[AR] A: Where does the garbage go?\nB: In the right bin, of course.\nA: And if you don't separate the waste?\nB: Then the neighbors get annoyed.",funFact:"[AR] Ab (off/away) + Fall (fall). Something that falls away, waste. 'Abfall trennen' (to separate waste) is a German commandment. Every German household sorts into at least four bins."},
        {type:"teach",trg:"der Abfalleimer",src:"[AR] the trash can",pos:"noun",gender:"m",note:"[AR] Abfall + Eimer (bucket). Germans have color-coded bins:\nyellow for packaging, blue for paper, brown for organic.",example:"A: Wo ist der Abfalleimer?\nB: In der Küche, neben dem Kühlschrank.\nA: Welcher Abfalleimer für Plastik?\nB: Der gelbe. Immer der gelbe.",exampleSrc:"[AR] A: Where is the trash can?\nB: In the kitchen, next to the fridge.\nA: Which trash can for plastic?\nB: The yellow one. Always the yellow one.",funFact:"[AR] Abfall + Eimer (bucket). Waste bucket. Germans have color-coded Abfalleimer: yellow for packaging, blue for paper, brown for organic. Putting wrong items in the wrong bin is a social crime."},
        {type:"teach",trg:"die Müllabfuhr",src:"[AR] garbage collection",pos:"noun",gender:"f",note:"[AR] Müll (trash) + Abfuhr (removal). In Germany, you pay\nper kilogram of trash. Less waste means lower bills.",example:"A: Wann kommt die Müllabfuhr?\nB: Montags für Restmüll.\nA: Und für Papier?\nB: Jeden zweiten Mittwoch.",exampleSrc:"[AR] A: When does garbage collection come?\nB: Mondays for residual waste.\nA: And for paper?\nB: Every other Wednesday.",funFact:"[AR] Müll (trash) + Abfuhr (removal). 'Die Müllabfuhr kommt montags' (The garbage truck comes on Mondays). In Germany, you pay per kilogram of trash. Less waste means lower bills."},
        {type:"teach",trg:"die Mülltonne",src:"[AR] the wheelie bin",pos:"noun",gender:"f",note:"[AR] Müll + Tonne (barrel/bin). Every German address has\nMülltonnen in four colors. Wrong sorting is a social crime.",example:"A: Die Mülltonne ist voll.\nB: Welche? Die gelbe oder die blaue?\nA: Die braune. Zu viel Bioabfall.\nB: Dann müssen wir kompostieren.",exampleSrc:"[AR] A: The wheelie bin is full.\nB: Which one? The yellow or the blue one?\nA: The brown one. Too much organic waste.\nB: Then we need to compost.",funFact:"[AR] Müll + Tonne (barrel/bin). Every German address has Mülltonnen in four colors. Putting the wrong item in the wrong Tonne is a social crime that neighbors will correct."},
        {type:"teach",trg:"das Plastik",src:"[AR] plastic",pos:"noun",gender:"n",note:"[AR] From Greek 'plastikos' (moldable). Neuter.\nGermany banned single-use plastic bags in 2022.",example:"A: Ist das aus Plastik?\nB: Ja, leider. Zu viel Plastik.\nA: Gibt es eine Alternative?\nB: Ja, aus Glas oder Holz.",exampleSrc:"[AR] A: Is that made of plastic?\nB: Yes, unfortunately. Too much plastic.\nA: Is there an alternative?\nB: Yes, made of glass or wood.",funFact:"[AR] From Greek 'plastikos' (moldable). Germany banned single-use plastic bags in 2022. 'Plastikfrei' (plastic-free) is a lifestyle movement. The Pfand system tackles plastic bottles."},
        {type:"teach",trg:"der Kunststoff",src:"[AR] plastic (formal), synthetic material",pos:"noun",gender:"m",note:"[AR] Kunst (art/artificial) + Stoff (material). The formal word\nfor plastic. Preferred in industry and science.",example:"A: Ist das Plastik oder Kunststoff?\nB: Das ist dasselbe. Kunststoff ist formeller.\nA: Was ist 'Kunststoffverpackung'?\nB: Verpackung aus Plastik. Für die gelbe Tonne.",exampleSrc:"[AR] A: Is that Plastik or Kunststoff?\nB: That is the same thing. Kunststoff is more formal.\nA: What is 'Kunststoffverpackung'?\nB: Packaging made of plastic. For the yellow bin.",funFact:"[AR] Kunst (art/artificial) + Stoff (material). Literally 'artificial material.' The formal German word for plastic. 'Kunststoffverpackung' (plastic packaging). More technical than Plastik, preferred in industry."},
        {type:"teach",trg:"das Holz",src:"[AR] wood",pos:"noun",gender:"n",note:"[AR] Cognate with English 'holt' (a small wood). 'Aus Holz' (made of wood).\nThe Black Forest is 60% of Baden-Württemberg's area.",example:"A: Woraus ist dieser Tisch?\nB: Aus Holz. Massives Eichenholz.\nA: Holz ist nachhaltig, oder?\nB: Ja, wenn es aus nachhaltiger Forstwirtschaft kommt.",exampleSrc:"[AR] A: What is this table made of?\nB: Wood. Solid oak wood.\nA: Wood is sustainable, right?\nB: Yes, if it comes from sustainable forestry.",funFact:"[AR] Cognate with English 'holt' (a small wood). 'Aus Holz' (made of wood). Germany's Black Forest (Schwarzwald) covers 60% of Baden-Württemberg. 'Holz hacken' (to chop wood) is a German weekend activity."},
        {type:"teach",trg:"das Metall",src:"[AR] metal",pos:"noun",gender:"n",note:"[AR] From Greek 'metallon' (mine/quarry). Neuter.\nGermany recycles 93% of metal packaging.",example:"A: Ist das aus Metall?\nB: Ja, aus Aluminium.\nA: Kommt das in die gelbe Tonne?\nB: Ja, Metall gehört zum Verpackungsmüll.",exampleSrc:"[AR] A: Is that made of metal?\nB: Yes, aluminum.\nA: Does that go in the yellow bin?\nB: Yes, metal belongs with packaging waste.",funFact:"[AR] From Greek 'metallon' (mine/quarry). Neuter. 'Altmetall' (scrap metal). Germany recycles 93% of metal packaging. 'Schwermetall' means both heavy metal (chemistry) and heavy metal (music)."},
        {type:"teach",trg:"das Material",src:"[AR] material",pos:"noun",gender:"n",note:"[AR] From Latin 'materialis.' Neuter. Plural: Materialien.\n'Baumaterial' (building material), 'Rohmaterial' (raw material).",example:"A: Welches Material ist das?\nB: Recyceltes Material.\nA: Aus welchem Material ist deine Tasche?\nB: Aus recyceltem Kunststoff.",exampleSrc:"[AR] A: What material is that?\nB: Recycled material.\nA: What material is your bag made of?\nB: From recycled synthetic material.",funFact:"[AR] From Latin 'materialis.' Neuter. 'Baumaterial' (building material), 'Rohmaterial' (raw material). International word, same in dozens of languages. Plural: Materialien."},
        {type:"teach",trg:"der Stoff",src:"[AR] material, fabric, substance",pos:"noun",gender:"m",note:"[AR] Triple meaning: 'Rohstoff' (raw material), 'Baumwollstoff'\n(cotton fabric), 'Unterrichtsstoff' (lesson material).",example:"A: Was für ein Stoff ist das?\nB: Baumwolle. Ein natürlicher Stoff.\nA: Ist Plastik auch ein Stoff?\nB: Ja, ein künstlicher Stoff.",exampleSrc:"[AR] A: What kind of material is that?\nB: Cotton. A natural material.\nA: Is plastic also a material?\nB: Yes, an artificial material.",funFact:"[AR] Triple meaning. 'Rohstoff' (raw material), 'Werkstoff' (working material), 'Baumwollstoff' (cotton fabric). Also: 'Unterrichtsstoff' (lesson material). Anything that constitutes something."},
        {type:"teach",trg:"die Ware",src:"[AR] goods, merchandise",pos:"noun",gender:"f",note:"[AR] 'Waren' (goods, plural). 'Warenhaus' (department store).\nRelated to English 'ware' (as in hardware, silverware).",example:"A: Woher kommen diese Waren?\nB: Aus China. Die meisten Waren kommen von dort.\nA: Gibt es lokale Waren?\nB: Ja, im Bio-Markt.",exampleSrc:"[AR] A: Where do these goods come from?\nB: From China. Most goods come from there.\nA: Are there local goods?\nB: Yes, at the organic market.",funFact:"[AR] 'Waren' (goods, plural). 'Hardware' and 'Software' were borrowed back from English. 'Warenhaus' (department store). Related to English 'ware' (as in hardware, silverware)."},
        {type:"teach",trg:"der Handel",src:"[AR] trade, commerce",pos:"noun",gender:"m",note:"[AR] From 'handeln' (to trade/act). 'Einzelhandel' (retail),\n'Großhandel' (wholesale), 'Außenhandel' (foreign trade).",example:"A: Der Handel mit China wächst.\nB: Und der faire Handel?\nA: Der wächst auch, aber langsamer.\nB: Handel ist wichtig für die Wirtschaft.",exampleSrc:"[AR] A: Trade with China is growing.\nB: And fair trade?\nA: That is growing too, but more slowly.\nB: Trade is important for the economy.",funFact:"[AR] From 'handeln' (to trade/act). 'Einzelhandel' (retail), 'Großhandel' (wholesale), 'Außenhandel' (foreign trade). 'Fair Handel' (fair trade) is a growing movement."},
        {type:"teach",trg:"der Händler",src:"[AR] dealer, trader",pos:"noun",gender:"m",note:"[AR] From Handel. 'Autohändler' (car dealer),\n'Buchhändler' (bookseller). The -er suffix creates the agent.",example:"A: Kennst du einen guten Händler?\nB: Ja, den Händler auf dem Wochenmarkt.\nA: Was verkauft der Händler?\nB: Obst und Gemüse aus der Region.",exampleSrc:"[AR] A: Do you know a good trader?\nB: Yes, the trader at the weekly market.\nA: What does the trader sell?\nB: Fruit and vegetables from the region.",funFact:"[AR] From Handel. 'Autohändler' (car dealer), 'Buchhändler' (bookseller). The -er suffix creates the person who does the action. A Händler handles Handel."},
        {type:"teach",trg:"die Händlerin",src:"[AR] dealer, trader (female)",pos:"noun",gender:"f",note:"[AR] The feminine form. Händler + -in.\nGerman consistently creates feminine forms with -in.",example:"A: Die Händlerin auf dem Markt ist nett.\nB: Ja, sie verkauft Bio-Produkte.\nA: Ist die Händlerin jeden Tag da?\nB: Nur dienstags und samstags.",exampleSrc:"[AR] A: The female trader at the market is nice.\nB: Yes, she sells organic products.\nA: Is the trader there every day?\nB: Only on Tuesdays and Saturdays.",funFact:"[AR] The feminine form. Händler + -in. 'Die Händlerin auf dem Markt' (the female trader at the market). German consistently creates feminine forms with -in for person nouns."},
        {type:"story",speaker:"lukas",mood:"sarcastic",art:"de-office-kitchen",trg:"Verumius, du hast eine Bananenschale in den Restmüll geworfen. Eine. Bananenschale. Das ist die braune Tonne. Willst du, dass die Nachbarin wieder einen Zettel schreibt?",src:"[AR] Verumius, you threw a banana peel in the residual waste. One. Banana peel. That goes in the brown bin. Do you want the neighbor lady to write another note?"},
        {type:"teach",trg:"der Export",src:"[AR] export",pos:"noun",gender:"m",note:"[AR] From Latin 'exportare' (to carry out). 'Made in Germany'\nis the world's most trusted export label.",example:"A: Was ist Deutschlands größter Export?\nB: Autos, Maschinen und Chemie.\nA: Ist der Export wichtig?\nB: Ja, er treibt die Wirtschaft an.",exampleSrc:"[AR] A: What is Germany's biggest export?\nB: Cars, machines, and chemicals.\nA: Is export important?\nB: Yes, it drives the economy.",funFact:"[AR] From Latin 'exportare' (to carry out). 'Made in Germany' is the world's most trusted export label. Germany is the third-largest exporter globally. Cars, machines, chemicals."},
        {type:"teach",trg:"der Import",src:"[AR] import",pos:"noun",gender:"m",note:"[AR] From Latin 'importare' (to carry in). The opposite of Export.\nGermany imports energy, raw materials, and coffee.",example:"A: Was importiert Deutschland?\nB: Viel Energie und Rohstoffe.\nA: Und Kaffee?\nB: Ja, Deutschland ist Europas größter Kaffeetrinker.",exampleSrc:"[AR] A: What does Germany import?\nB: A lot of energy and raw materials.\nA: And coffee?\nB: Yes, Germany is Europe's biggest coffee consumer.",funFact:"[AR] From Latin 'importare' (to carry in). The opposite of Export. 'Importware' (imported goods). Germany imports energy, raw materials, and coffee. Germans are Europe's biggest coffee drinkers."},
        {type:"teach",trg:"die Industrie",src:"[AR] industry",pos:"noun",gender:"f",note:"[AR] From Latin 'industria' (diligence). 'Schwerindustrie'\n(heavy industry). 'Industrie 4.0' is Germany's digital strategy.",example:"A: Die Industrie verbraucht viel Energie.\nB: Ja, besonders die Schwerindustrie.\nA: Gibt es grüne Industrie?\nB: Ja, immer mehr Firmen werden nachhaltig.",exampleSrc:"[AR] A: Industry uses a lot of energy.\nB: Yes, especially heavy industry.\nA: Is there green industry?\nB: Yes, more and more companies are becoming sustainable.",funFact:"[AR] From Latin 'industria' (diligence). 'Schwerindustrie' (heavy industry). Germany's Ruhrgebiet was Europe's industrial heart. 'Industrie 4.0' is Germany's digital manufacturing strategy."},
        {type:"teach",trg:"die Produktion",src:"[AR] production",pos:"noun",gender:"f",note:"[AR] From Latin 'productio.' The -tion ending is always feminine\nin German and always stressed on the last syllable.",example:"A: Die Produktion läuft gut.\nB: Ja, aber sie verbraucht viel Strom.\nA: Können wir die Produktion umstellen?\nB: Auf erneuerbare Energie, ja.",exampleSrc:"[AR] A: Production is going well.\nB: Yes, but it uses a lot of electricity.\nA: Can we switch the production?\nB: To renewable energy, yes.",funFact:"[AR] From Latin 'productio.' 'Massenproduktion' (mass production). 'Die Produktion einstellen' (to stop production). The -tion ending is always feminine in German and always stressed on the last syllable."},
        {type:"teach",trg:"produzieren",src:"[AR] to produce",pos:"verb",gender:null,note:"[AR] The -ieren verb from Produktion. Regular conjugation.\n'In Deutschland produziert' (produced in Germany).",example:"A: Was produziert diese Fabrik?\nB: Solarpanels. Alles ökologisch.\nA: Produzieren sie auch für den Export?\nB: Ja, weltweit.",exampleSrc:"[AR] A: What does this factory produce?\nB: Solar panels. All ecological.\nA: Do they also produce for export?\nB: Yes, worldwide.",funFact:"[AR] The -ieren verb from Produktion. Regular conjugation. 'In Deutschland produziert' (produced in Germany). 'Überproduzieren' (to overproduce). Reliable borrowed verb."},
        {type:"teach",trg:"alternativ",src:"[AR] alternative",pos:"adj",gender:null,note:"[AR] From Latin 'alternare.' 'Alternative Energien' (alternative energies).\n'Die Alternative' (noun) means the alternative option.",example:"A: Gibt es alternative Energien?\nB: Ja, Wind und Sonne.\nA: Sind alternative Materialien teurer?\nB: Manchmal, aber sie sind besser für die Umwelt.",exampleSrc:"[AR] A: Are there alternative energies?\nB: Yes, wind and sun.\nA: Are alternative materials more expensive?\nB: Sometimes, but they are better for the environment.",funFact:"[AR] From Latin 'alternare.' 'Alternative Energien' (alternative energies), 'alternative Medizin' (alternative medicine). 'Die Alternative' (the noun) means the alternative option."},
        {type:"teach",trg:"die Gelbe Tonne",src:"[AR] the yellow recycling bin",pos:"noun",gender:"f",note:"[AR] For packaging waste (Verpackung): plastic, aluminum, tetra paks.\nPart of Germany's Duales System (recycling system).",example:"A: Wohin kommt der Joghurtbecher?\nB: In die Gelbe Tonne.\nA: Und die Zeitung?\nB: In die Blaue Tonne. Papier ist blau.",exampleSrc:"[AR] A: Where does the yogurt cup go?\nB: In the yellow bin.\nA: And the newspaper?\nB: In the blue bin. Paper is blue.",funFact:"[AR] Germany's color-coded bin system: Gelbe Tonne (packaging), Blaue Tonne (paper), Braune Tonne (organic), Schwarze Tonne (residual waste). Getting it wrong can earn you a stern lecture from your neighbors."},
        {type:"mc",q:"Dein deutscher Nachbar schimpft, weil du einen Joghurtbecher in die falsche Tonne geworfen hast. In welche Tonne gehört Verpackung?",opts:["Braune Tonne","Gelbe Tonne","Blaue Tonne","Schwarze Tonne"],ans:"Gelbe Tonne",hint:"[AR] Which color bin is for Verpackung and Kunststoff? Not blue (paper) and not brown (organic)."},
        {type:"fb",s:"Dieser Tisch ist aus {1} gemacht.",a:["Holz"],opts:["Holz","Metall","Luft","Handel"],hint:"[AR] What material is a table usually made of? Think of trees.",sSrc:"[AR] This table is made of wood."},
        {type:"match",pairs:[
            {trg:"Handel",src:"trade"},
            {trg:"Export",src:"export"},
            {trg:"Industrie",src:"industry"},
            {trg:"Produktion",src:"production"}
          ]},
        {type:"story",speaker:"verumius",mood:"determined",art:"de-office-kitchen",trg:"Vier Tonnen, vier Farben, null Fehler. Mia wäre stolz. Lukas nennt mich den Mülldiktator. Ich nehme das als Kompliment.",src:"[AR] Four bins, four colors, zero mistakes. Mia would be proud. Lukas calls me the trash dictator. I take that as a compliment."}
      ]},
    {id:"deu_r22l3",title:"Der Pfand-Meister",icon:"🎯",xp:15,board:true,steps:[
        {type:"intro",title:"Der Pfand-Meister",desc:"[AR] Remember Unit 4? Verumius stood helplessly in front of the Pfandautomat. Today he is a pro. Along the way, learn an important grammar point: Partizip I as adjective.",goals:[
            "[AR] Learn 18 words about danger, protection, and research",
            "[AR] Understand Partizip I as adjective (die steigende Temperatur)",
            "[AR] See how far Verumius has come since Unit 4"
          ]},
        {type:"story",speaker:"narrator",mood:"proud",art:"de-rewe-pfand",trg:"REWE, Mittwochmorgen. Verumius schiebt sechs Flaschen in den Pfandautomaten. Ohne zu zögern, ohne nachzudenken. Vor einem Jahr stand er ratlos vor genau dieser Maschine. Heute sammelt der lachende Verumius seinen Bon und geht zur Kasse.",src:"[AR] REWE, Wednesday morning. Verumius feeds six bottles into the deposit machine. Without hesitating, without thinking. A year ago he stood helplessly in front of this very machine. Today the laughing Verumius collects his receipt and walks to the checkout."},
        {type:"teach",trg:"das Abgas",src:"[AR] exhaust gas, emission",pos:"noun",gender:"n",note:"[AR] Ab (away) + Gas. The gas that goes away from the engine.\n'Abgasnormen' (emission standards) are strict in Germany.",example:"A: Die Abgase hier sind schrecklich.\nB: Ja, zu viele Autos.\nA: Müssen wir die Abgase reduzieren?\nB: Unbedingt. Für bessere Luft.",exampleSrc:"[AR] A: The exhaust fumes here are terrible.\nB: Yes, too many cars.\nA: Do we have to reduce emissions?\nB: Absolutely. For better air.",funFact:"[AR] Ab (away) + Gas. Exhaust gas. 'Autoabgase' (car exhaust fumes). The word says what it is: gas that goes away from the engine. 'Abgasnormen' (emission standards) are strict in Germany."},
        {type:"teach",trg:"die Gefahr",src:"[AR] danger",pos:"noun",gender:"f",note:"[AR] 'In Gefahr' (in danger). 'Lebensgefahr' (mortal danger).\nFrom Old High German 'fara' (ambush).",example:"A: Ist das eine Gefahr für die Umwelt?\nB: Ja, eine große Gefahr.\nA: Wie groß ist die Gefahr?\nB: Sehr groß. Wir müssen handeln.",exampleSrc:"[AR] A: Is that a danger for the environment?\nB: Yes, a big danger.\nA: How big is the danger?\nB: Very big. We need to act.",funFact:"[AR] From Old High German 'fara' (ambush). 'In Gefahr' (in danger). 'Lebensgefahr' (mortal danger). 'Gefährlich' (dangerous). Danger originally meant an unexpected attack."},
        {type:"teach",trg:"die Katastrophe",src:"[AR] catastrophe, disaster",pos:"noun",gender:"f",note:"[AR] From Greek 'katastrophe' (overturning). Germans say\n'Das ist eine Katastrophe!' for any major problem.",example:"A: Die Überschwemmung war eine Katastrophe.\nB: Ja, eine Naturkatastrophe.\nA: Gibt es mehr Katastrophen als früher?\nB: Ja, wegen des Klimawandels.",exampleSrc:"[AR] A: The flood was a catastrophe.\nB: Yes, a natural disaster.\nA: Are there more catastrophes than before?\nB: Yes, because of climate change.",funFact:"[AR] From Greek 'katastrophe' (overturning). 'Naturkatastrophe' (natural disaster), 'Umweltkatastrophe' (environmental disaster). Germans say 'Das ist eine Katastrophe!' for any major problem, from floods to late trains."},
        {type:"teach",trg:"die Krise",src:"[AR] crisis",pos:"noun",gender:"f",note:"[AR] From Greek 'krisis' (decision/turning point). A Krise is\na turning point, not necessarily the end.",example:"A: Wir haben eine Klimakrise.\nB: Und eine Energiekrise.\nA: Jede Krise ist auch eine Chance.\nB: Stimmt. Wir müssen uns ändern.",exampleSrc:"[AR] A: We have a climate crisis.\nB: And an energy crisis.\nA: Every crisis is also an opportunity.\nB: True. We need to change.",funFact:"[AR] From Greek 'krisis' (decision/turning point). 'Klimakrise' (climate crisis), 'Wirtschaftskrise' (economic crisis). A Krise is a turning point, not necessarily the end. It demands a decision."},
        {type:"teach",trg:"der Schutz",src:"[AR] protection",pos:"noun",gender:"m",note:"[AR] From 'schützen' (to protect). 'Umweltschutz,' 'Datenschutz,'\n'Mutterschutz.' Germans protect everything with a compound.",example:"A: Umweltschutz ist wichtig.\nB: Und Datenschutz auch.\nA: Was ist Mutterschutz?\nB: Schutz für schwangere Frauen bei der Arbeit.",exampleSrc:"[AR] A: Environmental protection is important.\nB: And data protection too.\nA: What is maternity protection?\nB: Protection for pregnant women at work.",funFact:"[AR] From 'schützen' (to protect). 'Umweltschutz' (environmental protection), 'Datenschutz' (data protection), 'Mutterschutz' (maternity protection). Germans protect everything with a compound."},
        {type:"teach",trg:"die Sicherheit",src:"[AR] safety, security",pos:"noun",gender:"f",note:"[AR] From 'sicher' (safe/certain). The -heit suffix creates abstract nouns.\n'Verkehrssicherheit' (traffic safety).",example:"A: Die Sicherheit am Arbeitsplatz ist wichtig.\nB: Ja, Sicherheit geht vor.\nA: Was bedeutet Lebensmittelsicherheit?\nB: Dass unser Essen sicher ist.",exampleSrc:"[AR] A: Safety at the workplace is important.\nB: Yes, safety comes first.\nA: What does food safety mean?\nB: That our food is safe.",funFact:"[AR] From 'sicher' (safe/certain). 'Verkehrssicherheit' (traffic safety), 'Lebensmittelsicherheit' (food safety). The -heit suffix creates abstract nouns. Sicher + heit = the state of being safe."},
        {type:"teach",trg:"die Forschung",src:"[AR] research",pos:"noun",gender:"f",note:"[AR] From 'forschen' (to research). Germany spends 3%+ of GDP\non Forschung. The Fraunhofer institutes are world-famous.",example:"A: Klimaforschung ist entscheidend.\nB: Ja, ohne Forschung keine Lösungen.\nA: Wer finanziert die Forschung?\nB: Meistens der Staat und die Industrie.",exampleSrc:"[AR] A: Climate research is crucial.\nB: Yes, without research no solutions.\nA: Who funds the research?\nB: Mostly the state and industry.",funFact:"[AR] From 'forschen' (to research). 'Klimaforschung' (climate research), 'Grundlagenforschung' (basic research). Germany spends 3%+ of GDP on Forschung. The Fraunhofer institutes are world-famous."},
        {type:"teach",trg:"die Forderung",src:"[AR] demand, requirement",pos:"noun",gender:"f",note:"[AR] From 'fordern' (to demand). Not to be confused with 'fördern'\n(to promote/support). One Umlaut changes everything.",example:"A: Die Forderung nach Klimaschutz wächst.\nB: Ja, die Leute fordern Veränderung.\nA: Was ist die wichtigste Forderung?\nB: Weniger Abgase bis 2030.",exampleSrc:"[AR] A: The demand for climate protection is growing.\nB: Yes, people are demanding change.\nA: What is the most important demand?\nB: Fewer emissions by 2030.",funFact:"[AR] From 'fordern' (to demand). Not to be confused with 'fördern' (to promote/support). One Umlaut changes demand into support. 'Die Forderung nach Klimaschutz' (the demand for climate protection)."},
        {type:"teach",trg:"die Umfrage",src:"[AR] survey, poll",pos:"noun",gender:"f",note:"[AR] Um (around) + Frage (question). Asking around.\n'Laut einer Umfrage' (according to a survey).",example:"A: Laut einer Umfrage recyceln 90% der Deutschen.\nB: Das überrascht mich nicht.\nA: Was sagt die Umfrage noch?\nB: Dass Klimaschutz Priorität Nummer eins ist.",exampleSrc:"[AR] A: According to a survey, 90% of Germans recycle.\nB: That doesn't surprise me.\nA: What else does the survey say?\nB: That climate protection is priority number one.",funFact:"[AR] Um (around) + Frage (question). Asking around. A survey or poll. 'Laut einer Umfrage' (according to a survey). Germans love Umfragen. Every news broadcast cites one."},
        {type:"teach",trg:"schützen",src:"[AR] to protect",pos:"verb",gender:null,note:"[AR] 'Die Umwelt schützen' (to protect the environment).\n'Sich schützen' (to protect oneself). Regular verb.",example:"A: Wie können wir die Umwelt schützen?\nB: Weniger Plastik benutzen.\nA: Und wie schützt du dich vor der Hitze?\nB: Ich bleibe im Schatten.",exampleSrc:"[AR] A: How can we protect the environment?\nB: Use less plastic.\nA: And how do you protect yourself from the heat?\nB: I stay in the shade.",funFact:"[AR] 'Die Umwelt schützen' (to protect the environment). 'Sich schützen' (to protect oneself). Regular verb. The ü-Umlaut gives it its distinctive German sound."},
        {type:"teach",trg:"warnen",src:"[AR] to warn",pos:"verb",gender:null,note:"[AR] Cognate with English 'warn.' 'Vor Gefahr warnen'\n(to warn of danger). Regular verb.",example:"A: Ich warne dich vor der Hitze.\nB: Danke, ich nehme Wasser mit.\nA: Der Wetterdienst warnt vor Sturm.\nB: Dann bleibe ich lieber zu Hause.",exampleSrc:"[AR] A: I warn you about the heat.\nB: Thanks, I'll bring water.\nA: The weather service warns of a storm.\nB: Then I'd rather stay home.",funFact:"[AR] Cognate with English 'warn.' 'Vor Gefahr warnen' (to warn of danger). 'Unwetterwarnung' (severe weather warning). Regular verb. The Wetter-App sends Warnungen constantly."},
        {type:"teach",trg:"fordern",src:"[AR] to demand",pos:"verb",gender:null,note:"[AR] No Umlaut. Different from 'fördern' (to support).\n'Wir fordern Klimaschutz' (We demand climate protection).",example:"A: Die Demonstranten fordern Klimaschutz.\nB: Was genau fordern sie?\nA: Weniger Abgase und mehr erneuerbare Energie.\nB: Das ist eine berechtigte Forderung.",exampleSrc:"[AR] A: The demonstrators demand climate protection.\nB: What exactly do they demand?\nA: Fewer emissions and more renewable energy.\nB: That is a legitimate demand.",funFact:"[AR] Different from 'fördern' (to support). No Umlaut here. 'Wir fordern Klimaschutz' (We demand climate protection). Regular verb. The missing dots change the meaning completely."},
        {type:"teach",trg:"vermeiden",src:"[AR] to avoid",pos:"verb",gender:null,note:"[AR] Irregular: vermied, vermieden. 'Plastik vermeiden' (to avoid plastic).\nThe ver- prefix intensifies 'meiden' (to shun).",example:"A: Wie kann man Plastik vermeiden?\nB: Stoffbeutel benutzen.\nA: Kann man Abfall ganz vermeiden?\nB: Nicht ganz, aber stark reduzieren.",exampleSrc:"[AR] A: How can you avoid plastic?\nB: Use cloth bags.\nA: Can you completely avoid waste?\nB: Not entirely, but reduce it significantly.",funFact:"[AR] Irregular: vermied, vermieden. 'Plastik vermeiden' (to avoid plastic). 'Fehler vermeiden' (to avoid mistakes). The ver- prefix intensifies 'meiden' (to shun)."},
        {type:"teach",trg:"verursachen",src:"[AR] to cause",pos:"verb",gender:null,note:"[AR] Ver- + Ursache (cause). 'Abgase verursachen Luftverschmutzung.'\nThe compound logic: to cause = to make into a cause.",example:"A: Was verursacht die Luftverschmutzung?\nB: Vor allem Abgase.\nA: Verursacht Plastik auch Probleme?\nB: Ja, besonders im Meer.",exampleSrc:"[AR] A: What causes the air pollution?\nB: Mainly exhaust fumes.\nA: Does plastic also cause problems?\nB: Yes, especially in the sea.",funFact:"[AR] Ver- + Ursache (cause). 'Abgase verursachen Luftverschmutzung' (Exhaust fumes cause air pollution). Regular verb. The compound logic: to cause = to make into a cause."},
        {type:"teach",trg:"verschmutzen",src:"[AR] to pollute, to dirty",pos:"verb",gender:null,note:"[AR] Ver- + Schmutz (dirt). 'Die Luft verschmutzen' (to pollute the air).\nVer- often means 'to make into' something.",example:"A: Autos verschmutzen die Luft.\nB: Und Fabriken verschmutzen das Wasser.\nA: Wer verschmutzt am meisten?\nB: Die Industrie, laut Statistik.",exampleSrc:"[AR] A: Cars pollute the air.\nB: And factories pollute the water.\nA: Who pollutes the most?\nB: Industry, according to statistics.",funFact:"[AR] Ver- + Schmutz (dirt). 'Die Luft verschmutzen' (to pollute the air). 'Umweltverschmutzung' (environmental pollution). Ver- often means 'to make into' something."},
        {type:"teach",trg:"giftig",src:"[AR] toxic, poisonous",pos:"adj",gender:null,note:"[AR] From 'Gift' (poison). False friend: English 'gift' = present.\nGerman 'Gift' = poison. Nobody's present.",example:"A: Ist das giftig?\nB: Ja, sehr giftig. Nicht anfassen!\nA: Giftiger Abfall ist gefährlich.\nB: Deshalb gibt es Sondermüll.",exampleSrc:"[AR] A: Is that toxic?\nB: Yes, very toxic. Don't touch!\nA: Toxic waste is dangerous.\nB: That's why there is hazardous waste.",funFact:"[AR] From 'Gift' (poison). 'Giftige Chemikalien' (toxic chemicals). Fun false friend: English 'gift' = present. German 'Gift' = poison. 'Giftmüll' (toxic waste) is nobody's present."},
        {type:"teach",trg:"ökologisch",src:"[AR] ecological",pos:"adj",gender:null,note:"[AR] From Greek 'oikos' (house) + 'logos' (study). Often shortened to\n'öko-' as prefix: 'Ökostrom' (green electricity).",example:"A: Ist dieses Produkt ökologisch?\nB: Ja, zu 100 Prozent ökologisch.\nA: Was bedeutet 'ökologisch' genau?\nB: Umweltfreundlich hergestellt.",exampleSrc:"[AR] A: Is this product ecological?\nB: Yes, 100 percent ecological.\nA: What does 'ecological' mean exactly?\nB: Produced in an environmentally friendly way.",funFact:"[AR] From Greek 'oikos' (house) + 'logos' (study). 'Ökologischer Landbau' (organic farming). Often shortened to 'öko-' as a prefix: 'Ökostrom' (green electricity)."},
        {type:"teach",trg:"sparsam",src:"[AR] thrifty, economical",pos:"adj",gender:null,note:"[AR] From 'sparen' (to save). Germans consider Sparsamkeit\n(thriftiness) a virtue. Being sparsam is a compliment.",example:"A: Bist du sparsam mit Wasser?\nB: Ja, ich dusche nur fünf Minuten.\nA: Das ist sehr sparsam.\nB: Sparsam sein ist gut für die Umwelt.",exampleSrc:"[AR] A: Are you economical with water?\nB: Yes, I only shower for five minutes.\nA: That is very economical.\nB: Being thrifty is good for the environment.",funFact:"[AR] From 'sparen' (to save). 'Sparsam mit Wasser umgehen' (to use water sparingly). Germans consider Sparsamkeit (thriftiness) a virtue. Being sparsam is a compliment."},
        {type:"story",speaker:"narrator",mood:"amused",art:"de-rewe-pfand",trg:"Die Kassiererin schaut Verumius an. 'Sie sortieren besser als die meisten Deutschen,' sagt sie. Verumius strahlt. Das ist das schönste Kompliment, das er je in diesem Land bekommen hat.",src:"[AR] The cashier looks at Verumius. 'You sort better than most Germans,' she says. Verumius beams. That is the most beautiful compliment he has ever received in this country."},
        {type:"tip",title:"Partizip I as Adjective: The -end Form",text:"[AR] German can turn any verb into an adjective describing an ongoing action. Formation: infinitive + d.\n\nsteigen (to rise) becomes steigend (rising)\nlachen (to laugh) becomes lachend (laughing)\nwachsen (to grow) becomes wachsend (growing)\n\nThen it declines like a normal adjective:\n- der steigende Preis (the rising price)\n- die wachsende Gefahr (the growing danger)\n- ein sinkendes Schiff (a sinking ship)\n\nLike English: 'the laughing man' = 'der lachende Mann.' Same logic, same word order. Partizip I always describes an ongoing action.",deepDive:{title:"Partizip I: formation and usage",text:"[AR] The Partizip I is formed by adding -d to the infinitive. It always describes an ongoing action happening at the same time as the main verb.\n\nImportant: The Partizip I is used primarily as an adjective in German. Unlike English, you cannot use it to form progressive tenses ('I am running'). German says 'Ich laufe' (I run/am running).\n\nAs an adjective, it declines normally:\n- der lachende Mann (nominative masculine)\n- die lachenden Männer (nominative plural)\n- mit steigendem Interesse (dative neuter)\n\nAs an adverb, it has no ending: 'Er ging lachend weg' (He left laughing)."}},
        {type:"mc",q:"'Die steigenden Temperaturen sind gefährlich.' Was bedeutet 'steigenden' hier?",opts:["fallen","average","rising","extreme"],ans:"rising",hint:"[AR] Steigen means 'to rise.' The -d ending plus an adjective ending describes an ongoing action."},
        {type:"fb",s:"Die wachsende {1} durch Abgase ist ein ernstes Problem.",a:["Gefahr"],opts:["Gefahr","Sicherheit","Forschung","Umfrage"],hint:"[AR] Which noun means 'danger'? Something that grows and threatens.",sSrc:"[AR] The growing danger from exhaust fumes is a serious problem."},
        {type:"mc",q:"Wie bildet man das Partizip I von 'schlafen' (to sleep)?",opts:["schläft","schlafen","geschlafen","schlafend"],ans:"schlafend",hint:"[AR] Take the infinitive and add -d. The formation is always the same."},
        {type:"story",speaker:"verumius",mood:"satisfied",art:"de-rewe-pfand",trg:"Sechs Flaschen, ein Euro fünfzig Pfand. Ich erinnere mich noch an meinen ersten Tag am Pfandautomaten. Heute? Heute bin ich der Pfand-Meister.",src:"[AR] Six bottles, one euro fifty deposit. I still remember my first day at the deposit machine. Today? Today I am the deposit master."}
      ]},
    {id:"deu_r22l4",title:"Grammatik der Natur",icon:"📚",xp:15,board:true,steps:[
        {type:"intro",title:"Grammatik der Natur",desc:"[AR] Today you learn two powerful grammar tools: Partizip II as adjective (das recycelte Papier) and lassen as causative verb (Ich lasse mein Auto reparieren).",goals:[
            "[AR] Understand Partizip II as adjective (der gelesene Brief)",
            "[AR] Learn lassen in three meanings: causative, permissive, and imperative",
            "[AR] Combine all three new grammar constructs"
          ]},
        {type:"story",speaker:"mia",mood:"encouraging",art:"de-office-conference",trg:"Verumius, deine Präsentation gestern war beeindruckend. Aber heute geht es um Grammatik. Du willst wie ein Berliner klingen? Dann musst du die verschmutzte Luft von der verschmutzenden Fabrik unterscheiden können.",src:"[AR] Verumius, your presentation yesterday was impressive. But today is about grammar. You want to sound like a Berliner? Then you need to be able to tell the polluted air from the polluting factory apart."},
        {type:"teach",trg:"die Fabrik",src:"[AR] factory",pos:"noun",gender:"f",note:"[AR] From Latin 'fabrica' (workshop). Many old Fabriken are\nnow museums or cultural centers in the Ruhrgebiet.",example:"A: Was produziert diese Fabrik?\nB: Solarpanels.\nA: Ist die Fabrik umweltfreundlich?\nB: Ja, sie nutzt nur Ökostrom.",exampleSrc:"[AR] A: What does this factory produce?\nB: Solar panels.\nA: Is the factory environmentally friendly?\nB: Yes, it uses only green electricity.",funFact:"[AR] From Latin 'fabrica' (workshop). 'Chemiefabrik' (chemical factory), 'Autofabrik' (car factory). The Ruhrgebiet had thousands. Many are now museums or cultural centers."},
        {type:"teach",trg:"das Kraftwerk",src:"[AR] power plant",pos:"noun",gender:"n",note:"[AR] Kraft (power) + Werk (work/plant). Germany is shutting down\nnuclear Kraftwerke and building wind and solar ones.",example:"A: Was ist ein Kraftwerk?\nB: Eine Anlage, die Strom produziert.\nA: Kohlekraftwerk oder Windkraftwerk?\nB: Windkraftwerke sind besser für die Umwelt.",exampleSrc:"[AR] A: What is a power plant?\nB: A facility that produces electricity.\nA: Coal power plant or wind power plant?\nB: Wind power plants are better for the environment.",funFact:"[AR] Kraft (power) + Werk (work/plant). 'Atomkraftwerk' (nuclear power plant), 'Kohlekraftwerk' (coal power plant). Germany is shutting down nuclear ones."},
        {type:"teach",trg:"die Anlage",src:"[AR] facility, plant, installation",pos:"noun",gender:"f",note:"[AR] From 'anlegen' (to lay out). 'Solaranlage' (solar installation),\n'Kläranlage' (water treatment plant). Context determines meaning.",example:"A: Was ist eine Solaranlage?\nB: Eine Anlage, die Sonnenlicht in Strom umwandelt.\nA: Hast du eine auf dem Dach?\nB: Ja, seit zwei Jahren.",exampleSrc:"[AR] A: What is a solar installation?\nB: A facility that converts sunlight into electricity.\nA: Do you have one on the roof?\nB: Yes, for two years.",funFact:"[AR] From 'anlegen' (to lay out). 'Solaranlage' (solar installation), 'Kläranlage' (water treatment plant), 'Geldanlage' (financial investment). Context determines which meaning."},
        {type:"teach",trg:"die Werbung",src:"[AR] advertising",pos:"noun",gender:"f",note:"[AR] From 'werben' (to advertise/court). 'Keine Werbung!'\non German mailboxes means no junk mail.",example:"A: Überall Werbung!\nB: Ja, zu viel Werbung.\nA: Keine Werbung bitte.\nB: Schreib das auf deinen Briefkasten.",exampleSrc:"[AR] A: Advertising everywhere!\nB: Yes, too much advertising.\nA: No advertising please.\nB: Write that on your mailbox.",funFact:"[AR] From 'werben' (to advertise/court). 'Werbung machen' (to advertise). 'Keine Werbung!' on German mailboxes means no junk mail. Werbung is both the industry and the ads."},
        {type:"teach",trg:"die Reklame",src:"[AR] advertising (informal/pejorative)",pos:"noun",gender:"f",note:"[AR] From French 'réclame.' Slightly old-fashioned or pejorative.\nUsed for flashy or aggressive ads.",example:"A: Was ist der Unterschied zwischen Werbung und Reklame?\nB: Reklame klingt negativer.\nA: Wie 'billige Reklame'?\nB: Genau. Werbung ist neutraler.",exampleSrc:"[AR] A: What is the difference between Werbung and Reklame?\nB: Reklame sounds more negative.\nA: Like 'cheap advertising'?\nB: Exactly. Werbung is more neutral.",funFact:"[AR] From French 'réclame.' Advertising, but slightly old-fashioned or pejorative. 'Reklame machen' sounds less professional than 'Werbung machen.' Used for flashy or aggressive ads."},
        {type:"teach",trg:"die Marke",src:"[AR] brand, stamp",pos:"noun",gender:"f",note:"[AR] 'Briefmarke' (postage stamp), 'Automarke' (car brand).\n'Deutsche Marken' are globally trusted.",example:"A: Welche Marke ist das?\nB: Eine deutsche Marke.\nA: Deutsche Marken sind beliebt.\nB: Ja, weltweit bekannt und vertraut.",exampleSrc:"[AR] A: What brand is that?\nB: A German brand.\nA: German brands are popular.\nB: Yes, known and trusted worldwide.",funFact:"[AR] 'Briefmarke' (postage stamp), 'Automarke' (car brand). 'Deutsche Marken' are globally trusted. The word comes from 'markieren' (to mark). A brand marks its products."},
        {type:"teach",trg:"das Modell",src:"[AR] model",pos:"noun",gender:"n",note:"[AR] From Italian 'modello.' Neuter. 'Geschäftsmodell' (business model),\n'Automodell' (car model).",example:"A: Welches Modell ist dein Auto?\nB: Ein Elektromodell.\nA: Dieses Modell ist gut für die Umwelt.\nB: Ja, null Abgase.",exampleSrc:"[AR] A: What model is your car?\nB: An electric model.\nA: This model is good for the environment.\nB: Yes, zero emissions.",funFact:"[AR] From Italian 'modello.' Neuter. 'Geschäftsmodell' (business model), 'Automodell' (car model). 'Ein Modell für Nachhaltigkeit' (a model for sustainability)."},
        {type:"teach",trg:"der Faktor",src:"[AR] factor",pos:"noun",gender:"m",note:"[AR] From Latin 'factor' (maker). 'Ein wichtiger Faktor.'\nInternational word, same in most European languages.",example:"A: Was ist der wichtigste Faktor?\nB: Der Energieverbrauch.\nA: Gibt es andere Faktoren?\nB: Ja, Transport und Produktion.",exampleSrc:"[AR] A: What is the most important factor?\nB: Energy consumption.\nA: Are there other factors?\nB: Yes, transport and production.",funFact:"[AR] From Latin 'factor' (maker). 'Ein wichtiger Faktor' (an important factor). 'Risikofaktor' (risk factor). International word, same in most European languages."},
        {type:"teach",trg:"die Stufe",src:"[AR] step, level, stage",pos:"noun",gender:"f",note:"[AR] 'Vorstufe' (preliminary stage), 'Entwicklungsstufe'\n(development stage). Also literally a stair step.",example:"A: Auf welcher Stufe sind wir?\nB: Stufe zwei von fünf.\nA: Vorsicht, Stufe!\nB: Danke, fast gestolpert.",exampleSrc:"[AR] A: What level are we at?\nB: Level two of five.\nA: Watch out, step!\nB: Thanks, almost tripped.",funFact:"[AR] 'Vorstufe' (preliminary stage), 'Entwicklungsstufe' (development stage). Also literally a stair step. 'Vorsicht, Stufe!' (Watch out, step!) is on signs everywhere."},
        {type:"teach",trg:"das Netz",src:"[AR] net, network",pos:"noun",gender:"n",note:"[AR] Cognate with English 'net.' 'Stromnetz' (power grid),\n'Ins Netz gehen' means to go online or to fall into a trap.",example:"A: Das Stromnetz ist überlastet.\nB: Zu viele Klimaanlagen.\nA: Wir brauchen ein besseres Netz.\nB: Ja, für Ökostrom.",exampleSrc:"[AR] A: The power grid is overloaded.\nB: Too many air conditioners.\nA: We need a better grid.\nB: Yes, for green electricity.",funFact:"[AR] Cognate with English 'net.' 'Internet' (internet), 'Stromnetz' (power grid). 'Ins Netz gehen' (to go into the net) means to go online. Also: to fall into a trap."},
        {type:"teach",trg:"das Netzwerk",src:"[AR] network",pos:"noun",gender:"n",note:"[AR] Netz + Werk (work). 'Soziales Netzwerk' (social network).\nGermans turned 'Netzwerken' into a verb for professional networking.",example:"A: Hast du ein gutes Netzwerk?\nB: Ja, beruflich und privat.\nA: Netzwerken ist wichtig.\nB: Besonders in der Umweltbranche.",exampleSrc:"[AR] A: Do you have a good network?\nB: Yes, professionally and privately.\nA: Networking is important.\nB: Especially in the environmental sector.",funFact:"[AR] Netz + Werk (work). 'Soziales Netzwerk' (social network). 'Ein Netzwerk aufbauen' (to build a network). Professional networking is 'Netzwerken.' Germans turned it into a verb."},
        {type:"teach",trg:"die Technik",src:"[AR] technology, technique",pos:"noun",gender:"f",note:"[AR] From Greek 'techne' (art/skill). Emphasizes practical application.\n'Informationstechnik' (IT).",example:"A: Welche Technik benutzt ihr?\nB: Moderne Solartechnik.\nA: Technik oder Technologie?\nB: Technik ist praktischer, Technologie theoretischer.",exampleSrc:"[AR] A: What technology do you use?\nB: Modern solar technology.\nA: Technik or Technologie?\nB: Technik is more practical, Technologie more theoretical.",funFact:"[AR] From Greek 'techne' (art/skill). 'Spitzentechnik' (cutting-edge technology). 'Informationstechnik' (IT). 'Technik' emphasizes practical application, 'Technologie' the science."},
        {type:"teach",trg:"die Technologie",src:"[AR] technology (scientific)",pos:"noun",gender:"f",note:"[AR] Technik + -logie (study of). More academic than Technik.\nThe -ie ending is always stressed.",example:"A: Umwelttechnologie ist die Zukunft.\nB: Ja, Biotechnologie auch.\nA: Was ist der Unterschied zu Technik?\nB: Technologie ist wissenschaftlicher.",exampleSrc:"[AR] A: Environmental technology is the future.\nB: Yes, biotechnology too.\nA: What is the difference from Technik?\nB: Technologie is more scientific.",funFact:"[AR] Technik + -logie (study of). 'Umwelttechnologie' (environmental technology), 'Biotechnologie' (biotechnology). More academic and theoretical than Technik. The -ie ending is always stressed."},
        {type:"teach",trg:"erhöhen",src:"[AR] to increase, to raise",pos:"verb",gender:null,note:"[AR] Er- + hoch (high). Transitive: someone raises something.\nCompare: steigen (intransitive, something rises on its own).",example:"A: Wir müssen die Effizienz erhöhen.\nB: Und die Kosten nicht erhöhen?\nA: Genau. Effizienz erhöhen, Kosten senken.\nB: Das ist der Plan.",exampleSrc:"[AR] A: We need to increase efficiency.\nB: And not increase costs?\nA: Exactly. Increase efficiency, reduce costs.\nB: That's the plan.",funFact:"[AR] Er- + hoch (high). 'Die Temperatur erhöhen' (to increase the temperature). Transitive: someone raises something. Compare: steigen (intransitive, something rises on its own)."},
        {type:"teach",trg:"fördern",src:"[AR] to promote, to support",pos:"verb",gender:null,note:"[AR] WITH Umlaut, unlike fordern (to demand). 'Erneuerbare Energien\nfördern.' 'Förderung' (funding/support).",example:"A: Wir fördern erneuerbare Energien.\nB: Wie fördert ihr das?\nA: Mit Geld und mit Technik.\nB: Gute Förderung macht den Unterschied.",exampleSrc:"[AR] A: We promote renewable energies.\nB: How do you promote that?\nA: With money and technology.\nB: Good support makes the difference.",funFact:"[AR] WITH Umlaut, unlike fordern (to demand). 'Erneuerbare Energien fördern' (to promote renewable energies). 'Förderung' (funding/support). One dot changes demand to support."},
        {type:"teach",trg:"protestieren",src:"[AR] to protest",pos:"verb",gender:null,note:"[AR] From Latin 'protestari.' Regular -ieren verb.\n'Fridays for Future' made Germany a global protest capital.",example:"A: Warum protestieren die Leute?\nB: Gegen den Klimawandel.\nA: Hilft protestieren?\nB: Es macht auf Probleme aufmerksam.",exampleSrc:"[AR] A: Why are the people protesting?\nB: Against climate change.\nA: Does protesting help?\nB: It draws attention to problems.",funFact:"[AR] From Latin 'protestari.' Regular -ieren verb. 'Gegen den Klimawandel protestieren' (to protest against climate change). 'Fridays for Future' started protests worldwide, including Germany."},
        {type:"teach",trg:"statistisch",src:"[AR] statistical",pos:"adj",gender:null,note:"[AR] From Statistik. 'Statistisch gesehen' (statistically speaking).\nThe -isch ending creates adjectives from nouns.",example:"A: Statistisch gesehen steigt die Temperatur.\nB: Ist das statistisch signifikant?\nA: Ja, über 50 Jahre gemessen.\nB: Dann ist es statistisch eindeutig.",exampleSrc:"[AR] A: Statistically speaking, the temperature is rising.\nB: Is that statistically significant?\nA: Yes, measured over 50 years.\nB: Then it is statistically clear.",funFact:"[AR] From Statistik. 'Statistisch gesehen' (statistically speaking). The -isch ending creates adjectives from nouns. 'Statistisch signifikant' (statistically significant)."},
        {type:"teach",trg:"durchschnittlich",src:"[AR] average, on average",pos:"adj",gender:null,note:"[AR] From Durchschnitt. The -lich ending on compound nouns.\n'Durchschnittlich 20 Grad' (an average of 20 degrees).",example:"A: Wie hoch ist die durchschnittliche Temperatur?\nB: Durchschnittlich 10 Grad in Deutschland.\nA: Das ist durchschnittlich?\nB: Ja, aber es wird wärmer.",exampleSrc:"[AR] A: What is the average temperature?\nB: On average 10 degrees in Germany.\nA: That is average?\nB: Yes, but it is getting warmer.",funFact:"[AR] From Durchschnitt. 'Durchschnittlich 20 Grad' (an average of 20 degrees). The -lich ending on compound nouns: Durchschnitt + lich = on average. Long but logical."},
        {type:"tip",title:"Partizip II as Adjective: The Completed Action",text:"[AR] You know the Partizip II from the Perfekt: 'Ich habe das Buch gelesen.' Now as an adjective:\n\ngelesen (read) becomes: der gelesene Brief (the read letter)\nrecycelt (recycled) becomes: das recycelte Papier (the recycled paper)\nverschmutzt (polluted) becomes: die verschmutzte Luft (the polluted air)\n\nDeclension like any adjective. The key difference from Partizip I:\n- Partizip I (ongoing): der lesende Mann (the man who IS reading)\n- Partizip II (completed): der gelesene Brief (the letter that HAS BEEN read)\n\nLike English: 'the broken window,' 'the recycled paper.'",deepDive:{title:"Partizip II: regular and irregular forms",text:"[AR] Regular verbs form the Partizip II with ge- + stem + -t:\nmachen → gemacht, recyceln → recycelt\n\nIrregular verbs use ge- + stem change + -en:\nlesen → gelesen, brechen → gebrochen\n\nVerbs with inseparable prefixes (ver-, be-, er-, zer-) skip ge-:\nverschmutzen → verschmutzt, zerstören → zerstört\n\nVerbs ending in -ieren also skip ge-:\nrecyceln → recycelt, produzieren → produziert\n\nAs adjectives, all forms decline normally:\nder verschmutzte Fluss (nominative)\nden verschmutzten Fluss (accusative)\ndem verschmutzten Fluss (dative)"}},
        {type:"tip",title:"Extended Participial Phrases",text:"[AR] German packs modifiers BEFORE the noun, framed between the article and the noun itself.\n\n- die [in Berlin lebende] Frau (the woman living in Berlin)\n- das [von Goethe geschriebene] Buch (the book written by Goethe)\n- der [seit Wochen geplante] Urlaub (the vacation planned for weeks)\n\nHow to read them: find the article, jump to the NOUN, then read everything in between.\nHow to build them: start with a relative clause, remove the relative pronoun, and place the participle with its ending right before the noun.",deepDive:{title:"Why German Does This",text:"[AR] English: 'The woman who lives in Berlin'\nFormal German: 'Die in Berlin lebende Frau'\n\nComplex information in a single noun phrase. Standard in academic writing.\nExtreme examples exist in legal texts.\nStart simple and build up.\n\nPractice converting:\n'Der Fluss, der verschmutzt ist' = 'Der verschmutzte Fluss'\n'Das Papier, das recycelt wurde' = 'Das recycelte Papier'\n'Die Frau, die in Berlin lebt' = 'Die in Berlin lebende Frau'"}},
        {type:"tip",title:"State Passive: The Result Passive",text:"[AR] Formation: sein + Partizip II\nPresent: ist geöffnet (is open)\nPast: war geöffnet (was open)\n\nFocus: the STATE or RESULT, not the process.\n\nProcess passive (werden): Das Fenster wird geöffnet.\n(Someone is opening it right now.)\n\nState passive (sein): Das Fenster ist geöffnet.\n(It is in an open state.)",deepDive:{title:"State Passive in Daily Life",text:"[AR] Many state passive forms look like adjective + sein:\nDas Geschäft ist geschlossen.\nDer Kaffee ist gekocht.\nIst der Kaffee fertig?\n\nThe boundary between state passive and adjective is fluid in daily life.\nFor the exam: focus on the difference werden (process) vs. sein (state)."}},
        {type:"tip",title:"bekommen-Passiv: The Recipient Becomes Subject",text:"[AR] Standard passive: Das Buch wird dem Kind geschenkt. (The book is given to the child.)\nbekommen passive: Das Kind bekommt das Buch geschenkt. (The child gets the book given.)\n\nThe RECIPIENT becomes the subject.\n\nVery common in spoken German.\nkriegen works identically: Das Kind kriegt das Buch geschenkt.",deepDive:{title:"When to Use the bekommen-Passive",text:"[AR] Use it when you want to emphasize the RECIPIENT.\nNatural with verbs of giving, sending, and explaining.\n\nStandard: Mir wurde geholfen. (I was helped.)\nbekommen: Ich bekam Hilfe. (I received help.)\n\nSome grammarians call it colloquial, but it is standard spoken German."}},
        {type:"tip",title:"sein + zu + Infinitiv and -bar Adjectives",text:"[AR] The construction sein plus zu plus infinitive has TWO meanings depending on context:\n- Possibility: Das ist zu schaffen. (That can be done.)\n- Necessity: Die Regeln sind zu beachten. (The rules must be followed.)\n\nThe suffix -bar works like English -able or -ible:\n- machbar (doable), lösbar (solvable), essbar (edible)\n\nAdding un- negates the meaning: unlösbar, unvorstellbar, unessbar."},
        {type:"verb_table",title:"Präsens: lassen (to let/have done/leave)",groups:[
            {label:"Singular",rows:[
                {pronoun:"ich",form:"lasse",src:"I let/have done"},
                {pronoun:"du",form:"lässt",src:"you let/have done"},
                {pronoun:"er/sie/es",form:"lässt",src:"he/she/it lets/has done"}
              ]},
            {label:"Plural",rows:[
                {pronoun:"wir",form:"lassen",src:"we let/have done"},
                {pronoun:"ihr",form:"lasst",src:"you all let/have done"},
                {pronoun:"sie/Sie",form:"lassen",src:"they/you(formal) let/have done"}
              ]}
          ],note:"[AR] Irregular vowel change: a → ä in du/er/sie/es. Past: ließ. Partizip II: gelassen (or lassen with another infinitive)."},
        {type:"tip",title:"lassen: Three Verbs in One",text:"[AR] Lassen has three different meanings:\n\n1. TO HAVE DONE: etwas machen lassen\n'Ich lasse mein Auto reparieren.' (I have my car repaired.)\n'Sie lässt sich die Haare schneiden.' (She has her hair cut.)\n\n2. TO ALLOW: jemanden etwas tun lassen\n'Lass mich erklären!' (Let me explain!)\n'Er lässt sie gehen.' (He lets her go.)\n\n3. TO LEAVE/STOP: aufhören, zurücklassen\n'Lass das!' (Stop that!)\n'Ich lasse den Schirm hier.' (I leave the umbrella here.)\n\nPassive alternative: sich lassen = can be done\n'Das lässt sich machen.' (That can be done.)",deepDive:{title:"lassen in compound tenses",text:"[AR] In the Perfekt, lassen has two Partizip II forms:\n\n1. As a main verb: gelassen\n'Ich habe den Hund zu Hause gelassen.' (I left the dog at home.)\n\n2. With another infinitive: lassen (double infinitive)\n'Ich habe mein Auto reparieren lassen.' (I had my car repaired.)\n\nThe double infinitive construction (two infinitives at the end) is standard in German. It also applies to modal verbs in Perfekt:\n'Ich habe arbeiten müssen.' (I had to work.)"}},
        {type:"mc",q:"'Das recycelte Papier kommt in die blaue Tonne.' Was beschreibt 'recycelte'?",opts:[
            "Papier, das sich selbst recycelt",
            "Papier, das gerade recycelt wird",
            "Papier, das recycelt werden soll",
            "Papier, das bereits recycelt wurde"
          ],ans:"Papier, das bereits recycelt wurde",hint:"[AR] Partizip II describes a completed action. The recycling has already happened."},
        {type:"fb",s:"Verumius {1} sein Fahrrad reparieren.",a:["lässt"],opts:["lässt","lassen","lasst","lass"],hint:"[AR] Third person singular. Which modal-like verb expresses having someone else perform an action for you?",sSrc:"[AR] Verumius has his bike repaired."},
        {type:"mc",q:"'Der lesende Mann' und 'der gelesene Brief.' Was ist der Unterschied?",opts:[
            "Partizip I ist laufende Handlung, Partizip II ist abgeschlossene Handlung",
            "Sie bedeuten dasselbe",
            "Partizip I ist für Personen, Partizip II für Dinge",
            "Partizip I ist Vergangenheit, Partizip II ist Gegenwart"
          ],ans:"Partizip I ist laufende Handlung, Partizip II ist abgeschlossene Handlung",hint:"[AR] The man is reading right now (ongoing). The letter was read (completed)."},
        {type:"drag_fill",s:"Mia {1} die {2} Dokumente kopieren.",blanks:{"1":"lässt","2":"fehlenden"},pool:["lässt","lasst","fehlenden","gefehlten","lassen"],hint:"[AR] Mia has someone copy the missing documents. Causative lassen (3rd person) + Partizip I (ongoing absence).",sSrc:"[AR] Mia has the missing documents copied."},
        {type:"story",speaker:"verumius",mood:"amused",art:"de-office-conference",trg:"Partizip I, Partizip II, lassen. Drei neue Werkzeuge. Ich lasse mein Gehirn kurz ausruhen. Das ist auch eine Form von lassen, oder?",src:"[AR] Partizip I, Partizip II, lassen. Three new tools. I will let my brain rest briefly. That is also a form of lassen, right?"}
      ]},
    {id:"deu_r22l5",title:"Bio oder Discounter?",icon:"🛒",xp:15,board:true,steps:[
        {type:"intro",title:"Bio oder Discounter?",desc:"[AR] Bio market or Aldi? Mia loves organic, Lukas shops at the discounter. Verumius compares. Learn household vocabulary and practice all three grammar constructs.",goals:[
            "[AR] Learn 20 new words about household and measurements",
            "[AR] Compare ecological and budget shopping",
            "[AR] Practice Partizip I, Partizip II, and lassen in new contexts"
          ]},
        {type:"story",speaker:"mia",mood:"passionate",art:"de-biomarkt",trg:"Schau dir das an! Dieses frisch gebackene Brot, die handgemachte Seife, der fair gehandelte Kaffee. Im Bio-Markt weißt du, woher alles kommt.",src:"[AR] Look at this! This freshly baked bread, the handmade soap, the fairly traded coffee. At the organic market you know where everything comes from."},
        {type:"story",speaker:"lukas",mood:"practical",art:"de-discounter",trg:"Mia, ich lasse mich nicht von schöner Verpackung täuschen. Ich kaufe meine Nudeln für 49 Cent und lasse den Rest auf dem Konto.",src:"[AR] Mia, I don't let myself be fooled by nice packaging. I buy my pasta for 49 cents and leave the rest in my account."},
        {type:"teach",trg:"das Waschmittel",src:"[AR] detergent",pos:"noun",gender:"n",note:"[AR] Wasch (wash) + Mittel (means/agent). Germany has strict\nWaschmittel regulations. Phosphate bans started here in the 1980s.",example:"A: Welches Waschmittel benutzt du?\nB: Ökologisches Waschmittel.\nA: Ist das besser für die Umwelt?\nB: Ja, weniger Chemie im Wasser.",exampleSrc:"[AR] A: Which detergent do you use?\nB: Ecological detergent.\nA: Is that better for the environment?\nB: Yes, fewer chemicals in the water.",funFact:"[AR] Wasch (wash) + Mittel (means/agent). Detergent. 'Ökologisches Waschmittel' (ecological detergent). Germany has strict Waschmittel regulations. Phosphate bans started here in the 1980s."},
        {type:"teach",trg:"die Batterie",src:"[AR] battery",pos:"noun",gender:"f",note:"[AR] From French 'batterie.' Germany collects used Batterien\nin special green boxes at every supermarket.",example:"A: Die Batterie ist leer.\nB: Wirf sie in die Sammelbox.\nA: Wo ist die Sammelbox?\nB: Am Eingang vom Supermarkt.",exampleSrc:"[AR] A: The battery is empty.\nB: Throw it in the collection box.\nA: Where is the collection box?\nB: At the entrance of the supermarket.",funFact:"[AR] From French 'batterie.' 'Batterie einlegen' (to insert a battery). 'Aufladbare Batterie' (rechargeable battery). Germany collects used Batterien in special green boxes at every supermarket."},
        {type:"teach",trg:"das Feuerzeug",src:"[AR] lighter",pos:"noun",gender:"n",note:"[AR] Feuer (fire) + Zeug (stuff/tool). Fire-tool.\n'Hast du ein Feuerzeug?' is a classic conversation starter.",example:"A: Hast du ein Feuerzeug?\nB: Ja, hier bitte.\nA: Wo kann ich ein Feuerzeug kaufen?\nB: An jeder Kasse.",exampleSrc:"[AR] A: Do you have a lighter?\nB: Yes, here you go.\nA: Where can I buy a lighter?\nB: At every checkout.",funFact:"[AR] Feuer (fire) + Zeug (stuff/tool). Fire-tool. A lighter. 'Hast du ein Feuerzeug?' is a classic conversation starter. Das Feuerzeug, neuter, like most -zeug compounds."},
        {type:"teach",trg:"das Streichholz",src:"[AR] match",pos:"noun",gender:"n",note:"[AR] Streich (stroke) + Holz (wood). Strike-wood.\nMore poetic than Feuerzeug: a stick you stroke into flame.",example:"A: Hast du Streichhölzer?\nB: Ja, in der Schublade.\nA: Streichhölzer oder Feuerzeug?\nB: Streichhölzer, die sind romantischer.",exampleSrc:"[AR] A: Do you have matches?\nB: Yes, in the drawer.\nA: Matches or lighter?\nB: Matches, they are more romantic.",funFact:"[AR] Streich (stroke) + Holz (wood). Strike-wood. A match. 'Streichhölzer anzünden' (to light matches). More poetic than Feuerzeug. The image: a stick of wood you stroke into flame."},
        {type:"story",speaker:"verumius",mood:"conflicted",art:"de-biomarkt",trg:"Mia nimmt die handgemachte Seife für 4,50 Euro. Lukas zeigt mir auf dem Handy die gleiche Seife beim Discounter für 89 Cent. Ich stehe zwischen beiden und frage mich: Was würde ein richtiger Berliner tun?",src:"[AR] Mia picks up the handmade soap for 4.50 euros. Lukas shows me the same soap at the discounter for 89 cents on his phone. I stand between them and wonder: what would a real Berliner do?"},
        {type:"teach",trg:"die Zange",src:"[AR] pliers, tongs",pos:"noun",gender:"f",note:"[AR] 'Beißzange' (cutting pliers), 'Zuckerzange' (sugar tongs).\n'Jemanden in die Zange nehmen' means to put the squeeze on someone.",example:"A: Hast du eine Zange?\nB: Ja, im Werkzeugkasten.\nA: Ich brauche die Zange für das Rohr.\nB: Hier, nimm die große.",exampleSrc:"[AR] A: Do you have pliers?\nB: Yes, in the toolbox.\nA: I need the pliers for the pipe.\nB: Here, take the big ones.",funFact:"[AR] 'Beißzange' (cutting pliers), 'Zuckerzange' (sugar tongs). 'Jemanden in die Zange nehmen' (to put the squeeze on someone). A gripping tool for work and idioms."},
        {type:"teach",trg:"das Rohr",src:"[AR] pipe, tube",pos:"noun",gender:"n",note:"[AR] 'Wasserrohr' (water pipe), 'Abflussrohr' (drain pipe).\nAlso means 'reed' (the plant). Plumbing runs on Rohre.",example:"A: Das Rohr ist kaputt.\nB: Welches Rohr?\nA: Das Wasserrohr in der Küche.\nB: Wir müssen einen Klempner rufen.",exampleSrc:"[AR] A: The pipe is broken.\nB: Which pipe?\nA: The water pipe in the kitchen.\nB: We need to call a plumber.",funFact:"[AR] 'Wasserrohr' (water pipe), 'Abflussrohr' (drain pipe). Also means 'reed' (the plant). 'Rohrleitung' (pipeline). 'Durch die Rohre' means through the pipes. Plumbing runs on Rohre."},
        {type:"teach",trg:"der Sand",src:"[AR] sand",pos:"noun",gender:"m",note:"[AR] Same as English. 'Sandstrand' (sandy beach).\n'Den Kopf in den Sand stecken' means to bury one's head in the sand.",example:"A: Der Sand am Strand ist weiß.\nB: Ja, wunderschöner Sand.\nA: Steck nicht den Kopf in den Sand.\nB: Du hast recht. Ich muss handeln.",exampleSrc:"[AR] A: The sand at the beach is white.\nB: Yes, beautiful sand.\nA: Don't bury your head in the sand.\nB: You're right. I need to act.",funFact:"[AR] Same word as English. 'Sandstrand' (sandy beach), 'Sandkasten' (sandbox). 'Den Kopf in den Sand stecken' (to bury one's head in the sand) works identically in both languages."},
        {type:"teach",trg:"der Stein",src:"[AR] stone",pos:"noun",gender:"m",note:"[AR] Cognate with English 'stone.' 'Edelstein' (gemstone).\n'Ein Stein vom Herzen' (relief, literally: a stone off the heart).",example:"A: Was ist das für ein Stein?\nB: Ein Edelstein. Sehr selten.\nA: Mir fällt ein Stein vom Herzen.\nB: Gut, dass du erleichtert bist.",exampleSrc:"[AR] A: What kind of stone is that?\nB: A gemstone. Very rare.\nA: A weight off my shoulders. (lit: A stone off my heart.)\nB: Good that you are relieved.",funFact:"[AR] Cognate with English 'stone.' 'Ziegelstein' (brick), 'Edelstein' (gemstone). 'Ein Stein vom Herzen' (a stone off the heart) means relief."},
        {type:"teach",trg:"das Grundstück",src:"[AR] plot of land, property",pos:"noun",gender:"n",note:"[AR] Grund (ground) + Stück (piece). A piece of ground.\nEvery Grundstück is in the Grundbuch (land registry).",example:"A: Wie groß ist das Grundstück?\nB: 500 Quadratmeter.\nA: Ein Grundstück in Berlin ist teuer.\nB: Sehr teuer. Besonders in Mitte.",exampleSrc:"[AR] A: How big is the plot of land?\nB: 500 square meters.\nA: A plot of land in Berlin is expensive.\nB: Very expensive. Especially in Mitte.",funFact:"[AR] Grund (ground) + Stück (piece). A piece of ground. Property/plot of land. 'Ein Grundstück kaufen' (to buy a plot). German property law is thorough. Every Grundstück is in the Grundbuch (land registry)."},
        {type:"teach",trg:"der Rasen",src:"[AR] lawn",pos:"noun",gender:"m",note:"[AR] 'Den Rasen mähen' (to mow the lawn). 'Betreten des Rasens\nverboten' (Keep off the grass) is on signs in every German park.",example:"A: Der Rasen muss gemäht werden.\nB: Nicht am Sonntag!\nA: Warum nicht?\nB: Rasen mähen am Sonntag ist verboten.",exampleSrc:"[AR] A: The lawn needs to be mowed.\nB: Not on Sunday!\nA: Why not?\nB: Mowing the lawn on Sunday is forbidden.",funFact:"[AR] 'Den Rasen mähen' (to mow the lawn). 'Betreten des Rasens verboten' (Keep off the grass) is on signs in every German park. Germans take their Rasen seriously."},
        {type:"teach",trg:"die Fläche",src:"[AR] area, surface",pos:"noun",gender:"f",note:"[AR] From 'flach' (flat). 'Grundfläche' (floor area),\n'Wasserfläche' (water surface). Measured in Quadratmetern.",example:"A: Wie groß ist die Fläche?\nB: 80 Quadratmeter.\nA: Die Fläche Deutschlands?\nB: Etwa 357.000 Quadratkilometer.",exampleSrc:"[AR] A: How big is the area?\nB: 80 square meters.\nA: The area of Germany?\nB: About 357,000 square kilometers.",funFact:"[AR] From 'flach' (flat). 'Grundfläche' (floor area), 'Wasserfläche' (water surface). Measured in Quadratmetern. 'Die Fläche Deutschlands' is about 357,000 square kilometers."},
        {type:"teach",trg:"die Hälfte",src:"[AR] half",pos:"noun",gender:"f",note:"[AR] From 'halb' (half). 'Zur Hälfte' (halfway).\nEnglish 'half' and German 'Hälfte' share the same Proto-Germanic root.",example:"A: Die Hälfte ist schon fertig.\nB: Und die andere Hälfte?\nA: Morgen. Die Hälfte der Arbeit ist geschafft.\nB: Gut, weiter so.",exampleSrc:"[AR] A: Half is already done.\nB: And the other half?\nA: Tomorrow. Half the work is done.\nB: Good, keep going.",funFact:"[AR] From 'halb' (half). 'Die Hälfte der Bevölkerung' (half the population). 'Zur Hälfte' (halfway). English 'half' and German 'Hälfte' share the same Proto-Germanic root."},
        {type:"teach",trg:"die Höhe",src:"[AR] height",pos:"noun",gender:"f",note:"[AR] From 'hoch' (high). 'Meereshöhe' (sea level). Also figuratively:\n'in voller Höhe' (in full amount).",example:"A: In welcher Höhe liegt Berlin?\nB: Etwa 34 Meter über dem Meeresspiegel.\nA: Das ist nicht sehr hoch.\nB: Nein, Berlin ist ziemlich flach.",exampleSrc:"[AR] A: At what height is Berlin?\nB: About 34 meters above sea level.\nA: That is not very high.\nB: No, Berlin is quite flat.",funFact:"[AR] From 'hoch' (high). 'In der Höhe' (at height). 'Meereshöhe' (sea level). Also figuratively: 'in voller Höhe' (in full amount). The Umlaut ö comes from the adjective hoch."},
        {type:"teach",trg:"die Länge",src:"[AR] length",pos:"noun",gender:"f",note:"[AR] From 'lang' (long). 'In die Länge ziehen' (to drag out).\nAdjective to abstract noun via Umlaut: lang becomes Länge.",example:"A: Wie ist die Länge des Flusses?\nB: 580 Kilometer.\nA: Zieh es nicht in die Länge!\nB: Okay, ich fasse mich kurz.",exampleSrc:"[AR] A: What is the length of the river?\nB: 580 kilometers.\nA: Don't drag it out!\nB: Okay, I'll keep it short.",funFact:"[AR] From 'lang' (long). 'In die Länge ziehen' (to drag out). 'Wellenlänge' (wavelength). Adjective to abstract noun via Umlaut: lang becomes Länge, just as hoch becomes Höhe."},
        {type:"teach",trg:"die Anzahl",src:"[AR] number (quantity)",pos:"noun",gender:"f",note:"[AR] An (at) + Zahl (number). More formal than 'Zahl' or 'Nummer.'\nUsed for countable quantities in statistics.",example:"A: Wie ist die Anzahl der Teilnehmer?\nB: 250.\nA: Die Anzahl steigt jedes Jahr.\nB: Ja, immer mehr Leute kommen.",exampleSrc:"[AR] A: What is the number of participants?\nB: 250.\nA: The number rises every year.\nB: Yes, more and more people come.",funFact:"[AR] An (at) + Zahl (number). 'Die Anzahl der Teilnehmer' (the number of participants). More formal than 'Zahl' or 'Nummer.' Used for countable quantities in statistics and reports."},
        {type:"teach",trg:"der Rand",src:"[AR] edge, margin, rim",pos:"noun",gender:"m",note:"[AR] 'Am Rand der Stadt' (on the edge of the city).\n'Außer Rand und Band' (out of control).",example:"A: Am Rand der Stadt gibt es Natur.\nB: Ja, Felder und Wiesen.\nA: Er ist außer Rand und Band.\nB: Total aufgeregt, ja.",exampleSrc:"[AR] A: On the edge of the city there is nature.\nB: Yes, fields and meadows.\nA: He is out of control.\nB: Totally excited, yes.",funFact:"[AR] 'Am Rand der Stadt' (on the edge of the city). 'Brillenrand' (frame of glasses). 'Außer Rand und Band' (out of control, literally out of edge and band)."},
        {type:"teach",trg:"der Schatten",src:"[AR] shadow, shade",pos:"noun",gender:"m",note:"[AR] Cognate with English 'shadow.' 'Im Schatten sitzen'\n(to sit in the shade). '30 Grad im Schatten' means it is really hot.",example:"A: Lass uns im Schatten sitzen.\nB: Ja, bei 35 Grad braucht man Schatten.\nA: Die Schattenseite der Industrie.\nB: Verschmutzung und Abfall.",exampleSrc:"[AR] A: Let's sit in the shade.\nB: Yes, at 35 degrees you need shade.\nA: The downside of industry.\nB: Pollution and waste.",funFact:"[AR] Cognate with English 'shadow' (from 'shade'). 'Im Schatten sitzen' (to sit in the shade). 'Schattenseite' (downside, literally shadow side). '30 Grad im Schatten' means it is really hot."},
        {type:"teach",trg:"verpacken",src:"[AR] to package",pos:"verb",gender:null,note:"[AR] Ver- + packen (to pack). 'Umweltfreundlich verpackt.'\n'Verpackungsmüll' is a major environmental topic.",example:"A: Wie ist das Produkt verpackt?\nB: In Plastik, leider.\nA: Kann man es anders verpacken?\nB: Ja, in Papier oder Karton.",exampleSrc:"[AR] A: How is the product packaged?\nB: In plastic, unfortunately.\nA: Can you package it differently?\nB: Yes, in paper or cardboard.",funFact:"[AR] Ver- + packen (to pack). 'Umweltfreundlich verpackt' (packaged in an eco-friendly way). 'Verpackungsmüll' (packaging waste) is a major environmental topic. Germany has strict Verpackungsverordnung."},
        {type:"teach",trg:"verbrauchen",src:"[AR] to consume, to use up",pos:"verb",gender:null,note:"[AR] Ver- + brauchen (to need). 'Strom verbrauchen.' The ver-\nprefix means using something until it is gone.",example:"A: Wie viel Strom verbrauchen wir?\nB: Zu viel.\nA: Wir müssen weniger verbrauchen.\nB: Ja, jeder Verbraucher muss sparen.",exampleSrc:"[AR] A: How much electricity do we use?\nB: Too much.\nA: We need to consume less.\nB: Yes, every consumer needs to save.",funFact:"[AR] Ver- + brauchen (to need). 'Strom verbrauchen' (to use electricity). 'Verbraucher' (consumer). The ver- prefix means using something until it is gone. Completely used up."},
        {type:"teach",trg:"künstlich",src:"[AR] artificial",pos:"adj",gender:null,note:"[AR] From 'Kunst' (art/artifice). 'Künstliches Licht' (artificial light).\n'Künstliche Intelligenz' (artificial intelligence).",example:"A: Ist das künstlich oder natürlich?\nB: Künstlich. Aus dem Labor.\nA: Künstliche Intelligenz ist überall.\nB: Ja, die Technologie wächst schnell.",exampleSrc:"[AR] A: Is that artificial or natural?\nB: Artificial. From the lab.\nA: Artificial intelligence is everywhere.\nB: Yes, the technology is growing fast.",funFact:"[AR] From 'Kunst' (art/artifice). 'Künstliches Licht' (artificial light). 'Künstliche Intelligenz' (artificial intelligence). What Kunst creates is künstlich. Not natural, but made by human skill."},
        {type:"mc",q:"Lukas sagt: 'Ich lasse mich nicht von schöner Verpackung täuschen.' Was meint er?",opts:[
            "Er lässt sich nicht von hübscher Verpackung hereinlegen",
            "Er lässt sich Verpackung herstellen",
            "Er hört auf zu verpacken",
            "Er lässt die Verpackung im Laden"
          ],ans:"Er lässt sich nicht von hübscher Verpackung hereinlegen",hint:"[AR] Sich etwas antun lassen. Täuschen means to deceive. Choose the colloquial synonym among the options."},
        {type:"story",speaker:"verumius",mood:"thoughtful",art:"de-biomarkt",trg:"Mia hat recht: Bio schmeckt besser. Lukas hat auch recht: Bio ist teurer. Mein Kompromiss? Bio-Gemüse, Discounter-Nudeln. Das Beste aus beiden Welten.",src:"[AR] Mia is right: organic tastes better. Lukas is also right: organic is more expensive. My compromise? Organic vegetables, discount pasta. The best of both worlds."}
      ]},
    {id:"deu_r22l6",title:"Ruhig du sagen",icon:"🤝",xp:15,board:true,steps:[
        {type:"intro",title:"Ruhig du sagen",desc:"[AR] A special moment: Yilmaz offers Verumius the Du. Along the way, learn weather and nature vocabulary and experience Mia's rare compliment.",goals:[
            "[AR] Learn 18 words about weather and nature",
            "[AR] Experience the Sie-to-du switch as a social milestone",
            "[AR] Practice all three grammar constructs in dialogue"
          ]},
        {type:"story",speaker:"yilmaz",mood:"warm",art:"de-vhs-corridor",trg:"Verumius... wir kennen uns jetzt seit fast einem Jahr. Du kannst ruhig du sagen.",src:"[AR] Verumius... we have known each other for almost a year now. You can go ahead and say du."},
        {type:"story",speaker:"verumius",mood:"surprised",art:"de-vhs-corridor",trg:"Das... das freut mich wirklich. Danke, Frau Yil... ich meine... danke, Elif.",src:"[AR] That... that really makes me happy. Thank you, Mrs. Yil... I mean... thank you, Elif."},
        {type:"story",speaker:"narrator",mood:"warm",art:"de-vhs-corridor",trg:"Ein stiller Moment im leeren Flur. Kein großer Moment für die Welt, aber ein entscheidender Moment für Verumius. Die vertraute Stimme seiner Lehrerin hat jetzt einen anderen Klang.",src:"[AR] A quiet moment in the empty hallway. Not a big moment for the world, but a decisive moment for Verumius. The familiar voice of his teacher now has a different sound."},
        {type:"teach",trg:"die Umgebung",src:"[AR] surroundings, area",pos:"noun",gender:"f",note:"[AR] Um (around) + Gebung (giving/area). 'Die nahe Umgebung'\n(the immediate surroundings). What is given around you.",example:"A: Wie ist die Umgebung hier?\nB: Sehr grün. Viel Natur.\nA: In der Umgebung von Berlin gibt es Seen.\nB: Ja, perfekt für den Sommer.",exampleSrc:"[AR] A: What are the surroundings like here?\nB: Very green. A lot of nature.\nA: In the Berlin area there are lakes.\nB: Yes, perfect for summer.",funFact:"[AR] Um (around) + Gebung (giving/area). Surroundings. 'Die nahe Umgebung' (the immediate surroundings). 'In der Umgebung von Berlin' (in the Berlin area). What is given around you."},
        {type:"teach",trg:"der Wetterbericht",src:"[AR] weather report",pos:"noun",gender:"m",note:"[AR] Wetter (weather) + Bericht (report). Germans check the\nWetterbericht religiously. Rain is always possible.",example:"A: Was sagt der Wetterbericht?\nB: Morgen Regen.\nA: Schon wieder?\nB: Ja, der Wetterbericht sagt immer Regen.",exampleSrc:"[AR] A: What does the weather report say?\nB: Rain tomorrow.\nA: Again?\nB: Yes, the weather report always says rain.",funFact:"[AR] Wetter (weather) + Bericht (report). 'Den Wetterbericht lesen' (to read the weather report). Germans check the Wetterbericht religiously. Rain is always possible."},
        {type:"teach",trg:"die Wettervorhersage",src:"[AR] weather forecast",pos:"noun",gender:"f",note:"[AR] Wetter + Vorhersage (forecast). Longer and more formal\nthan Wetterbericht. Used in official contexts.",example:"A: Laut Wettervorhersage wird es heiß.\nB: Wie heiß?\nA: 38 Grad.\nB: Die Wettervorhersage macht mir Angst.",exampleSrc:"[AR] A: According to the weather forecast, it will be hot.\nB: How hot?\nA: 38 degrees.\nB: The weather forecast scares me.",funFact:"[AR] Wetter + Vorhersage (forecast). 'Laut Wettervorhersage regnet es morgen' (According to the forecast, it rains tomorrow). Longer and more formal than Wetterbericht."},
        {type:"teach",trg:"der Sturm",src:"[AR] storm",pos:"noun",gender:"m",note:"[AR] Cognate with English 'storm.' 'Sturmwarnung' (storm warning).\nGermany's worst storms come from the North Sea.",example:"A: Ein Sturm kommt!\nB: Wie stark?\nA: Sehr stark. Sturmwarnung.\nB: Dann bleiben wir zu Hause.",exampleSrc:"[AR] A: A storm is coming!\nB: How strong?\nA: Very strong. Storm warning.\nB: Then we stay home.",funFact:"[AR] Cognate with English 'storm.' 'Sturmwarnung' (storm warning). 'Im Sturm erobern' (to take by storm). Germany's worst storms come from the North Sea. Orkan = hurricane-force storm."},
        {type:"teach",trg:"der Donner",src:"[AR] thunder",pos:"noun",gender:"m",note:"[AR] Related to the god Thor/Donar. 'Donnerstag' (Thursday) =\nThor's day. 'Donnerwetter!' is an exclamation of surprise.",example:"A: Hörst du den Donner?\nB: Ja, ein Gewitter kommt.\nA: Donner und Blitz!\nB: Donnerwetter, das war laut!",exampleSrc:"[AR] A: Do you hear the thunder?\nB: Yes, a thunderstorm is coming.\nA: Thunder and lightning!\nB: Wow, that was loud!",funFact:"[AR] Related to the god Thor/Donar. 'Donnerstag' (Thursday) = Thor's day. 'Donnerwetter!' is an exclamation of surprise (literally: thunder weather!). Both languages name Thursday after the thunder god."},
        {type:"teach",trg:"der Alarm",src:"[AR] alarm, alert",pos:"noun",gender:"m",note:"[AR] From Italian 'all'arme' (to arms!). 'Feueralarm' (fire alarm),\n'Alarmstufe rot' (red alert). 'Alarm schlagen' (to sound the alarm).",example:"A: Alarm! Feueralarm!\nB: Schnell, raus aus dem Gebäude.\nA: Ist das ein echter Alarm?\nB: Ja, die Feuerwehr kommt schon.",exampleSrc:"[AR] A: Alarm! Fire alarm!\nB: Quick, out of the building.\nA: Is that a real alarm?\nB: Yes, the fire department is already coming.",funFact:"[AR] From Italian 'all'arme' (to arms!). 'Feueralarm' (fire alarm), 'Alarmstufe rot' (red alert). 'Alarm schlagen' (to sound the alarm). International word with military origins."},
        {type:"teach",trg:"die Störung",src:"[AR] disruption, disturbance",pos:"noun",gender:"f",note:"[AR] From 'stören' (to disturb). Deutsche Bahn's favorite word:\n'Wegen einer Störung...' (Due to a disruption...).",example:"A: Wegen einer Störung fährt kein Zug.\nB: Schon wieder eine Störung?\nA: Ja, eine technische Störung.\nB: Das ist typisch für die Bahn.",exampleSrc:"[AR] A: Due to a disruption, no train is running.\nB: Another disruption?\nA: Yes, a technical disruption.\nB: That is typical for the railway.",funFact:"[AR] From 'stören' (to disturb). 'Betriebsstörung' (service disruption). Deutsche Bahn's favorite word: 'Wegen einer Störung...' (Due to a disruption...). Every train delay starts here."},
        {type:"teach",trg:"die Unterstützung",src:"[AR] support",pos:"noun",gender:"f",note:"[AR] Unter (under) + stützen (to support). Support from below.\n'Um Unterstützung bitten' (to ask for support).",example:"A: Brauchst du Unterstützung?\nB: Ja, finanzielle Unterstützung.\nA: Ich biete dir meine Unterstützung an.\nB: Danke, das bedeutet mir viel.",exampleSrc:"[AR] A: Do you need support?\nB: Yes, financial support.\nA: I offer you my support.\nB: Thank you, that means a lot to me.",funFact:"[AR] Unter (under) + stützen (to support). Support from below. 'Finanzielle Unterstützung' (financial support). 'Um Unterstützung bitten' (to ask for support). You hold something up from underneath."},
        {type:"teach",trg:"der Tierpark",src:"[AR] zoo, animal park",pos:"noun",gender:"m",note:"[AR] Tier (animal) + Park. 'Der Berliner Tierpark' is the largest\nlandscape zoo in Europe. Emphasizes the park-like setting.",example:"A: Warst du schon im Tierpark?\nB: Ja, der Berliner Tierpark ist toll.\nA: Ist Tierpark dasselbe wie Zoo?\nB: Ähnlich, aber der Tierpark ist mehr wie ein Park.",exampleSrc:"[AR] A: Have you been to the animal park?\nB: Yes, the Berlin Tierpark is great.\nA: Is Tierpark the same as Zoo?\nB: Similar, but the Tierpark is more like a park.",funFact:"[AR] Tier (animal) + Park. 'Der Berliner Tierpark' is the largest landscape zoo in Europe. Different from 'Zoo' (which is also used). Tierpark emphasizes the park-like setting."},
        {type:"teach",trg:"beschädigen",src:"[AR] to damage",pos:"verb",gender:null,note:"[AR] Be- + Schaden (damage). 'Der Sturm hat das Dach beschädigt.'\nRegular verb. The be- prefix makes 'Schaden' transitive.",example:"A: Der Sturm hat das Dach beschädigt.\nB: Wie schlimm?\nA: Ziemlich beschädigt.\nB: Wir müssen es reparieren lassen.",exampleSrc:"[AR] A: The storm damaged the roof.\nB: How bad?\nA: Quite damaged.\nB: We need to have it repaired.",funFact:"[AR] Be- + Schaden (damage). 'Der Sturm hat das Dach beschädigt' (The storm damaged the roof). Regular verb. The be- prefix makes 'Schaden' into a transitive verb."},
        {type:"teach",trg:"brennen",src:"[AR] to burn",pos:"verb",gender:null,note:"[AR] Irregular: brannte, gebrannt. Cognate with English 'burn.'\n'Es brennt!' (It's burning!) is what you shout during a fire.",example:"A: Es brennt! Ruf die Feuerwehr!\nB: Wo brennt es?\nA: In der Küche. Das Essen brennt.\nB: Schnell, Wasser!",exampleSrc:"[AR] A: It's burning! Call the fire department!\nB: Where is it burning?\nA: In the kitchen. The food is burning.\nB: Quick, water!",funFact:"[AR] Irregular: brannte, gebrannt. Cognate with English 'burn.' 'Es brennt!' (It is burning!) is what you shout during a fire. 'Brennholz' (firewood). 'Brennnessel' (stinging nettle, the burning nettle)."},
        {type:"teach",trg:"donnern",src:"[AR] to thunder",pos:"verb",gender:null,note:"[AR] From Donner. 'Es donnert' (it is thundering).\nAlso: 'gegen die Tür donnern' (to bang on the door).",example:"A: Es donnert seit einer Stunde.\nB: Ja, ein starkes Gewitter.\nA: Wer donnert da gegen die Tür?\nB: Der Nachbar. Er will rein.",exampleSrc:"[AR] A: It has been thundering for an hour.\nB: Yes, a strong thunderstorm.\nA: Who is banging on the door?\nB: The neighbor. He wants to come in.",funFact:"[AR] From Donner. 'Es donnert' (it is thundering). Also: 'gegen die Tür donnern' (to bang on the door). Regular despite its mythological origins. Thor would approve."},
        {type:"teach",trg:"blitzen",src:"[AR] to flash (lightning)",pos:"verb",gender:null,note:"[AR] From 'Blitz' (lightning). 'Es blitzt' (there is lightning).\nSpeed cameras are called 'Blitzer' because they flash.",example:"A: Es blitzt!\nB: Und es donnert auch.\nA: Vorsicht, Blitzer!\nB: Zu spät. Geblitzt.",exampleSrc:"[AR] A: Lightning!\nB: And it is thundering too.\nA: Watch out, speed camera!\nB: Too late. Got flashed.",funFact:"[AR] From 'Blitz' (lightning). 'Es blitzt' (there is lightning). 'Blitzschnell' (lightning fast). Also: speed cameras are called 'Blitzer' because they flash when they catch you."},
        {type:"teach",trg:"hageln",src:"[AR] to hail",pos:"verb",gender:null,note:"[AR] From 'Hagel' (hail). 'Es hagelt' (it is hailing).\n'Es hagelt Beschwerden' (complaints are hailing down).",example:"A: Es hagelt!\nB: Stell das Auto in die Garage.\nA: Hagel kann Autos zerstören.\nB: Ja, und auch Gewächshäuser.",exampleSrc:"[AR] A: It is hailing!\nB: Put the car in the garage.\nA: Hail can destroy cars.\nB: Yes, and also greenhouses.",funFact:"[AR] From 'Hagel' (hail). 'Es hagelt' (it is hailing). Hail can destroy cars, crops, and greenhouse roofs. 'Es hagelt Beschwerden' (complaints are hailing down) is used figuratively."},
        {type:"teach",trg:"trocknen",src:"[AR] to dry",pos:"verb",gender:null,note:"[AR] From 'trocken' (dry). 'Wäsche trocknen' (to dry laundry).\nGermans often air-dry laundry rather than using a dryer.",example:"A: Die Wäsche muss trocknen.\nB: Draußen oder drinnen?\nA: Draußen. Die Sonne trocknet schnell.\nB: Aber nur, wenn es nicht regnet.",exampleSrc:"[AR] A: The laundry needs to dry.\nB: Outside or inside?\nA: Outside. The sun dries quickly.\nB: But only if it doesn't rain.",funFact:"[AR] From 'trocken' (dry). 'Wäsche trocknen' (to dry laundry). Germans often air-dry laundry rather than using a Trockner (dryer). Energy-saving and laundry-friendly."},
        {type:"teach",trg:"retten",src:"[AR] to rescue, to save",pos:"verb",gender:null,note:"[AR] 'Die Feuerwehr rettet Menschen.' 'Die Umwelt retten.'\n'Rettungswagen' (ambulance). A verb of heroic action.",example:"A: Die Feuerwehr rettet ein Kind.\nB: Helden!\nA: Können wir die Umwelt noch retten?\nB: Ja, aber wir müssen jetzt handeln.",exampleSrc:"[AR] A: The fire department is rescuing a child.\nB: Heroes!\nA: Can we still save the environment?\nB: Yes, but we need to act now.",funFact:"[AR] 'Die Feuerwehr rettet Menschen' (The fire department rescues people). 'Die Umwelt retten' (to save the environment). 'Rettungswagen' (ambulance). A verb of heroic action."},
        {type:"teach",trg:"steil",src:"[AR] steep",pos:"adj",gender:null,note:"[AR] 'Ein steiler Hügel' (a steep hill). 'Steile Karriere'\n(meteoric career). 'Steile These' (bold claim).",example:"A: Der Weg ist sehr steil.\nB: Ja, ziemlich steil hier.\nA: Seine Karriere ist steil.\nB: Von null auf hundert.",exampleSrc:"[AR] A: The path is very steep.\nB: Yes, quite steep here.\nA: His career is steep.\nB: From zero to a hundred.",funFact:"[AR] 'Ein steiler Hügel' (a steep hill). 'Steile Karriere' (meteoric career). 'Steile These' (bold claim). From physical incline to figurative extremes."},
        {type:"teach",trg:"wild",src:"[AR] wild",pos:"adj",gender:null,note:"[AR] Same word, same meaning as English. 'Wilde Tiere' (wild animals).\nGermany has more wild boars than any European country.",example:"A: Gibt es wilde Tiere in Berlin?\nB: Ja, Wildschweine in den Vororten.\nA: Wild!\nB: Wirklich wild. Pass auf im Park.",exampleSrc:"[AR] A: Are there wild animals in Berlin?\nB: Yes, wild boars in the suburbs.\nA: Wild!\nB: Really wild. Be careful in the park.",funFact:"[AR] Same word, same meaning as English. 'Wilde Tiere' (wild animals), 'Wildnis' (wilderness). 'Wildschwein' (wild boar) roam Berlin's suburbs. Germany has more wild boars than any European country."},
        {type:"story",speaker:"verumius",mood:"emotional",art:"de-park-bench",trg:"Elif. Nicht mehr Frau Yilmaz. Elif. Ich sitze auf einer Parkbank und wiederhole den Namen leise. Ein ganzes Jahr für drei Silben. Aber diese drei Silben bedeuten: du gehörst dazu.",src:"[AR] Elif. No longer Mrs. Yilmaz. Elif. I sit on a park bench and repeat the name quietly. A whole year for three syllables. But those three syllables mean: you belong."},
        {type:"story",speaker:"mia",mood:"warm",art:"de-park-bench",trg:"Du bist ein richtiger Berliner geworden. Du trennst deinen Müll, du lässt dein Fahrrad reparieren statt ein neues zu kaufen, und du kennst jeden Pfandautomaten in Kreuzberg.",src:"[AR] You have become a real Berliner. You separate your trash, you have your bike repaired instead of buying a new one, and you know every deposit machine in Kreuzberg."},
        {type:"mc",q:"Yilmaz sagt: 'Du kannst ruhig du sagen.' Welchen sozialen Meilenstein stellt das dar?",opts:[
            "Sie bittet ihn, sie formell anzusprechen",
            "Sie bittet ihn, leiser zu sprechen",
            "Sie korrigiert seine Grammatik",
            "Sie bietet informelle Anrede als Zeichen der Nähe an"
          ],ans:"Sie bietet informelle Anrede als Zeichen der Nähe an",hint:"[AR] Switching from Sie to du is a personal milestone in German culture."}
      ]},
    {id:"deu_r22l7",title:"Umwelt-Quiz",icon:"🏆",xp:15,board:true,steps:[
        {type:"intro",title:"Umwelt-Quiz",desc:"[AR] Test your environmental German. Prove you have mastered Partizip I and II as adjectives and can use lassen in all its meanings.",goals:[
            "[AR] Test your environmental vocabulary",
            "[AR] Prove mastery of Partizip I and II",
            "[AR] Show you can use lassen in all its meanings"
          ]},
        {type:"story",speaker:"narrator",mood:"dramatic",art:"de-park-cleanup",trg:"Samstag im Volkspark Friedrichshain. Mia hat eine Aufräumaktion organisiert. Verumius ist dabei. Lukas auch, aber er hat die falschen Tüten mitgebracht. Natürlich.",src:"[AR] Saturday in Volkspark Friedrichshain. Mia has organized a cleanup event. Verumius is there. Lukas too, but he brought the wrong bags. Of course."},
        {type:"teach",trg:"der Dreck",src:"[AR] dirt, filth",pos:"noun",gender:"m",note:"[AR] More colloquial than Schmutz. 'Im Dreck sitzen' (to be in trouble).\nNorthern German uses Dreck, southern prefers Schmutz.",example:"A: Hier ist überall Dreck.\nB: Ja, wir müssen sauber machen.\nA: Er sitzt im Dreck.\nB: Ja, große Probleme.",exampleSrc:"[AR] A: There is dirt everywhere.\nB: Yes, we need to clean.\nA: He is in trouble. (lit: sitting in dirt)\nB: Yes, big problems.",funFact:"[AR] More colloquial than Schmutz. 'Im Dreck sitzen' (to be in trouble, literally: sitting in dirt). 'Dreckig' (dirty/filthy). Northern German uses Dreck, southern prefers Schmutz."},
        {type:"teach",trg:"der Schmutz",src:"[AR] dirt, grime",pos:"noun",gender:"m",note:"[AR] More formal than Dreck. 'Schmutzig' (dirty).\n'Schmutzwasser' (dirty water).",example:"A: Der Schmutz muss weg.\nB: Ja, alles ist schmutzig.\nA: Schmutzwasser darf nicht in den Fluss.\nB: Deshalb gibt es Kläranlagen.",exampleSrc:"[AR] A: The dirt has to go.\nB: Yes, everything is dirty.\nA: Dirty water must not go into the river.\nB: That's why there are water treatment plants.",funFact:"[AR] More formal than Dreck. 'Schmutzig' (dirty). 'Schmutzwasser' (dirty water). The Sch- sound gives it a squelchy feel. German onomatopoeia at work."},
        {type:"teach",trg:"der Staub",src:"[AR] dust",pos:"noun",gender:"m",note:"[AR] Cognate with English 'dust' (via different path).\n'Staubsauger' (vacuum cleaner, literally dust-sucker).",example:"A: Überall Staub!\nB: Wo ist der Staubsauger?\nA: Im Schrank. Staub wischen ist wichtig.\nB: Zu Staub werden wir alle.",exampleSrc:"[AR] A: Dust everywhere!\nB: Where is the vacuum cleaner?\nA: In the closet. Dusting is important.\nB: We all turn to dust eventually.",funFact:"[AR] Cognate with English 'dust' (via different path). 'Staubsauger' (vacuum cleaner, literally dust-sucker). 'Staub wischen' (to dust). 'Zu Staub werden' (to turn to dust)."},
        {type:"teach",trg:"der Hügel",src:"[AR] hill",pos:"noun",gender:"m",note:"[AR] Diminutive feel from the -el ending. 'Ameisenhügel' (anthill).\nGermany is full of Hügel in the Mittelgebirge region.",example:"A: Lass uns auf den Hügel steigen.\nB: Der Hügel ist ziemlich steil.\nA: Von oben sieht man die ganze Umgebung.\nB: Das lohnt sich.",exampleSrc:"[AR] A: Let's climb the hill.\nB: The hill is quite steep.\nA: From the top you can see the whole area.\nB: It's worth it.",funFact:"[AR] Diminutive feel from the -el ending, though not a true diminutive. 'Ameisenhügel' (anthill). Germany's landscape is full of Hügel, especially in the Mittelgebirge region."},
        {type:"teach",trg:"das Gebirge",src:"[AR] mountain range",pos:"noun",gender:"n",note:"[AR] Ge- + Berg (mountain) collective. 'Hochgebirge' (high mountains).\nThe Ge- prefix creates a collective: many mountains together.",example:"A: Die Alpen sind ein Hochgebirge.\nB: Ja, das höchste Gebirge Europas.\nA: Und das Mittelgebirge?\nB: Niedriger, aber auch schön.",exampleSrc:"[AR] A: The Alps are a high mountain range.\nB: Yes, the highest mountain range in Europe.\nA: And the medium-height mountains?\nB: Lower, but also beautiful.",funFact:"[AR] Ge- + Berg (mountain) collective. Mountain range. 'Hochgebirge' (high mountains), 'Mittelgebirge' (medium-height mountains). The Ge- prefix creates a collective: many mountains together."},
        {type:"story",speaker:"lukas",mood:"confused",art:"de-park-cleanup",trg:"Verumius, ich habe eine Frage. Warum gibt es Mülltüten, die sich 'biologisch abbaubar' nennen, aber dann nicht in die Biotonne dürfen? Das ist doch eine Katastrophe für die Logik!",src:"[AR] Verumius, I have a question. Why are there trash bags that call themselves 'biodegradable' but then aren't allowed in the organic bin? That is a catastrophe for logic!"},
        {type:"teach",trg:"das Tal",src:"[AR] valley",pos:"noun",gender:"n",note:"[AR] Cognate with English 'dale.' 'Rheintal' (Rhine valley).\n'Bergauf, bergab, durch jedes Tal.'",example:"A: Das Tal ist wunderschön.\nB: Ja, das Rheintal ist berühmt.\nA: Durch jedes Tal fließt ein Fluss.\nB: Meistens, ja.",exampleSrc:"[AR] A: The valley is beautiful.\nB: Yes, the Rhine valley is famous.\nA: Through every valley flows a river.\nB: Mostly, yes.",funFact:"[AR] Cognate with English 'dale.' 'Rheintal' (Rhine valley), 'Moseltal' (Moselle valley). 'Bergauf, bergab, durch jedes Tal' (uphill, downhill, through every valley)."},
        {type:"teach",trg:"der Mond",src:"[AR] moon",pos:"noun",gender:"m",note:"[AR] Cognate with English 'moon' and 'month' (Monat).\nSame root: time was measured by moons. 'Vollmond' (full moon).",example:"A: Schau, der Vollmond!\nB: Wunderschön. Mondschein.\nA: Bei Vollmond schlafe ich schlecht.\nB: Ich auch. Komisch, oder?",exampleSrc:"[AR] A: Look, the full moon!\nB: Beautiful. Moonlight.\nA: I sleep badly during a full moon.\nB: Me too. Strange, right?",funFact:"[AR] Cognate with English 'moon' and 'month' (Monat). Same root: time was measured by moons. 'Vollmond' (full moon), 'Halbmond' (crescent/half moon). 'Mondschein' (moonshine/moonlight)."},
        {type:"teach",trg:"der Stern",src:"[AR] star",pos:"noun",gender:"m",note:"[AR] Cognate with English 'star' (via Latin 'stella').\n'Sternschnuppe' (shooting star). Also a famous German news magazine.",example:"A: Schau dir die Sterne an!\nB: So viele Sterne heute.\nA: Hast du eine Sternschnuppe gesehen?\nB: Ja, wünsch dir was!",exampleSrc:"[AR] A: Look at the stars!\nB: So many stars today.\nA: Did you see a shooting star?\nB: Yes, make a wish!",funFact:"[AR] Cognate with English 'star' (via Latin 'stella'). 'Sternschnuppe' (shooting star, literally star-snip). 'Fünf-Sterne-Hotel' (five-star hotel). Stern is also a famous German news magazine."},
        {type:"teach",trg:"der Lärm",src:"[AR] noise",pos:"noun",gender:"m",note:"[AR] From French 'alarme.' 'Lärmschutz' (noise protection).\nGermans have strict Ruhezeiten (quiet hours).",example:"A: Der Lärm ist unerträglich.\nB: Ja, zu viel Lärm.\nA: Lärm am Sonntag ist verboten.\nB: Ruhezeiten müssen eingehalten werden.",exampleSrc:"[AR] A: The noise is unbearable.\nB: Yes, too much noise.\nA: Noise on Sunday is forbidden.\nB: Quiet hours must be observed.",funFact:"[AR] From French 'alarme.' 'Lärm machen' (to make noise). 'Lärmschutz' (noise protection). Germans have strict Ruhezeiten (quiet hours). Lawn mowing on Sunday? That is illegal Lärm."},
        {type:"teach",trg:"das Gas",src:"[AR] gas",pos:"noun",gender:"n",note:"[AR] Coined by Dutch chemist Van Helmont in the 1600s from Greek 'chaos.'\n'Erdgas' (natural gas). 'Gas geben' (to step on the gas).",example:"A: Heizen wir mit Gas?\nB: Ja, Erdgas.\nA: Gas geben!\nB: Wir fahren schon schnell genug.",exampleSrc:"[AR] A: Do we heat with gas?\nB: Yes, natural gas.\nA: Step on it!\nB: We are already going fast enough.",funFact:"[AR] Coined by Dutch chemist Van Helmont in the 1600s from Greek 'chaos.' 'Erdgas' (natural gas), 'Abgas' (exhaust gas). 'Gas geben' (to step on the gas/accelerate). A Dutch-invented word used worldwide."},
        {type:"teach",trg:"zerstören",src:"[AR] to destroy",pos:"verb",gender:null,note:"[AR] Zer- + stören (to disturb). The zer- prefix means apart/to pieces.\nStronger than beschädigen (to damage). Total destruction.",example:"A: Der Sturm hat alles zerstört.\nB: Komplett zerstört?\nA: Ja, das Haus ist zerstört.\nB: Das ist eine Katastrophe.",exampleSrc:"[AR] A: The storm destroyed everything.\nB: Completely destroyed?\nA: Yes, the house is destroyed.\nB: That is a catastrophe.",funFact:"[AR] Zer- + stören (to disturb). The zer- prefix means apart/to pieces. 'Die Umwelt zerstören' (to destroy the environment). Stronger than beschädigen (to damage). Total destruction."},
        {type:"teach",trg:"weltenweit",src:"[AR] worldwide (literary)",pos:"adj",gender:null,note:"[AR] Welten (worlds) + weit (wide). A poetic variant of weltweit.\n'Weltenweite Probleme.' The extra -en- adds a literary tone.",example:"A: Das Problem ist weltenweit.\nB: Ja, nicht nur in Deutschland.\nA: Weltenweite Zusammenarbeit ist nötig.\nB: Alle Länder müssen helfen.",exampleSrc:"[AR] A: The problem is worldwide.\nB: Yes, not only in Germany.\nA: Worldwide cooperation is needed.\nB: All countries must help.",funFact:"[AR] Welten (worlds) + weit (wide). A poetic variant of weltweit. Both are used. 'Weltenweite Probleme' (worldwide problems). The extra -en- adds a literary tone."},
        {type:"teach",trg:"weltweit",src:"[AR] worldwide",pos:"adj",gender:null,note:"[AR] Welt + weit. The standard form. 'Weltweit bekannt'\n(known worldwide). More common than weltenweit.",example:"A: Dieses Problem ist weltweit.\nB: Ja, überall auf der Welt.\nA: Weltweit einzigartig.\nB: Es gibt nichts Vergleichbares.",exampleSrc:"[AR] A: This problem is worldwide.\nB: Yes, everywhere in the world.\nA: Unique worldwide.\nB: There is nothing comparable.",funFact:"[AR] Welt + weit. The standard form. 'Weltweit bekannt' (known worldwide). More common than weltenweit in everyday use. 'Weltweit einzigartig' (unique worldwide)."},
        {type:"teach",trg:"zentral",src:"[AR] central",pos:"adj",gender:null,note:"[AR] From Latin 'centralis.' 'Zentrale Lage' (central location).\n'Zentralheizung' (central heating).",example:"A: Die Lage ist sehr zentral.\nB: Ja, direkt in der Stadtmitte.\nA: Hast du Zentralheizung?\nB: Ja, in jedem Zimmer.",exampleSrc:"[AR] A: The location is very central.\nB: Yes, right in the city center.\nA: Do you have central heating?\nB: Yes, in every room.",funFact:"[AR] From Latin 'centralis.' 'Zentrale Lage' (central location). 'Zentralheizung' (central heating). Every German apartment listing mentions whether it has Zentralheizung."},
        {type:"story",speaker:"mia",mood:"commanding",art:"de-park-cleanup",trg:"Okay, Leute! Plastik in die gelbe Tüte, Glas in die grüne, Zigarettenstummel extra. Lukas, das ist kein Picknick. Lass die Brezel liegen und hilf!",src:"[AR] Okay, people! Plastic in the yellow bag, glass in the green one, cigarette butts separate. Lukas, this is not a picnic. Put the pretzel down and help!"},
        {type:"mc",q:"'Die steigenden Kosten und die wachsende Verschmutzung sind ein Problem.' Welche zwei Formen sind Partizip I?",opts:["steigenden und Verschmutzung","Kosten und Problem","steigenden und wachsende","wachsende und Problem"],ans:"steigenden und wachsende",hint:"[AR] Partizip I = Infinitiv + d + Adjektivendung. Suche nach dem -end-Muster."},
        {type:"fb",s:"Die {1} Luft in der Stadt ist ein Gesundheitsrisiko.",a:["verschmutzte"],opts:["verschmutzte","verschmutzende","verschmutzen","Verschmutzung"],hint:"[AR] The air HAS BEEN polluted. Partizip II as adjective. Completed action.",sSrc:"[AR] The polluted air in the city is a health risk."},
        {type:"mc",q:"Welcher Satz benutzt lassen als KAUSATIV (etwas machen lassen)?",opts:["Er lässt den Hund im Auto","Lass das!","Ich lasse mein Fahrrad reparieren","Lass mich in Ruhe!"],ans:"Ich lasse mein Fahrrad reparieren",hint:"[AR] Causative means: someone else performs the action for you. Who is repairing the bike?"},
        {type:"drag_fill",s:"Der {1} Fluss und die {2} Fabrik sind ein Problem.",blanks:{"1":"verschmutzte","2":"brennende"},pool:["verschmutzte","brennende","verschmutzende","gebrannt","brennen"],hint:"[AR] The river was polluted (completed). The factory is burning right now (ongoing). Which is P1, which P2?",sSrc:"[AR] The polluted river and the burning factory are a problem."},
        {type:"mc",q:"Es donnert, es blitzt, und der Wind ist extrem stark. Welches Wort beschreibt dieses Wetter?",opts:["Sturm","Durchschnitt","Schatten","Umgebung"],ans:"Sturm",hint:"[AR] Thunder, lightning, extreme wind. Think about what we call a severe weather event."},
        {type:"fb",s:"Das Problem {1} sich lösen.",a:["lässt"],opts:["lässt","lassen","lass","lasst"],hint:"[AR] Sich lassen + Infinitiv = can be done. Think of the third person singular form.",sSrc:"[AR] The problem can be solved."},
        {type:"match",pairs:[
            {trg:"der lachende Mann",src:"Partizip I (ongoing)"},
            {trg:"der gelesene Brief",src:"Partizip II (completed)"},
            {trg:"Ich lasse reparieren",src:"lassen causative"},
            {trg:"Das lässt sich machen",src:"sich lassen passive"}
          ]},
        {type:"story",speaker:"lukas",mood:"sheepish",art:"de-park-cleanup",trg:"Mia, ich habe die falschen Tüten mitgebracht. Aber ich habe drei Stunden lang Dreck gesammelt! Das zählt doch auch, oder?",src:"[AR] Mia, I brought the wrong bags. But I collected dirt for three hours! That counts too, right?"},
        {type:"story",speaker:"mia",mood:"amused",art:"de-park-cleanup",trg:"Es zählt, Lukas. Es zählt. Nächstes Mal bringe ich dir die richtigen Tüten mit. Und eine Liste.",src:"[AR] It counts, Lukas. It counts. Next time I will bring you the right bags. And a list."}
      ]},
    {id:"deu_r22l8",title:"Ein richtiger Berliner",icon:"🌳",xp:15,board:true,steps:[
        {type:"intro",title:"Ein richtiger Berliner",desc:"[AR] The final chapter of this unit. Verumius looks back on a year in Berlin. Learn the last environment and emergency words and prepare for the next level.",goals:[
            "[AR] Learn 18 final words on environment and emergencies",
            "[AR] Reflect on Verumius's growth in Berlin",
            "[AR] Prepare for the B1 exam journey ahead"
          ]},
        {type:"story",speaker:"narrator",mood:"nostalgic",art:"de-kreuzberg-street",trg:"Ein Sonntagmorgen in Kreuzberg. Verumius geht zum Pfandautomaten, kauft Bio-Brot auf dem Markt und grüßt seine Nachbarn auf Deutsch. Ein normaler Tag. Vor einem Jahr wäre nichts davon normal gewesen.",src:"[AR] A Sunday morning in Kreuzberg. Verumius goes to the deposit machine, buys organic bread at the market, and greets his neighbors in German. A normal day. A year ago none of this would have been normal."},
        {type:"teach",trg:"der Protest",src:"[AR] protest",pos:"noun",gender:"m",note:"[AR] From Latin 'protestari' (to declare publicly). 'Klimaprotest.'\n'Fridays for Future' made Berlin a global protest capital.",example:"A: Warst du beim Klimaprotest?\nB: Ja, tausende Leute waren da.\nA: Protest hilft!\nB: Ja, er macht auf Probleme aufmerksam.",exampleSrc:"[AR] A: Were you at the climate protest?\nB: Yes, thousands of people were there.\nA: Protesting helps!\nB: Yes, it draws attention to problems.",funFact:"[AR] From Latin 'protestari' (to declare publicly). 'Klimaprotest' (climate protest). 'Gegen etwas protestieren' (to protest against something). 'Fridays for Future' made Berlin a global protest capital."},
        {type:"teach",trg:"die Alternative",src:"[AR] alternative",pos:"noun",gender:"f",note:"[AR] From Latin 'alternare.' 'Alternativlos' was Germany's\nun-word of the year 2010. Means there is no other option.",example:"A: Gibt es eine Alternative?\nB: Ja, erneuerbare Energie.\nA: Manche sagen, es gibt keine Alternative.\nB: 'Alternativlos' ist ein gefährliches Wort.",exampleSrc:"[AR] A: Is there an alternative?\nB: Yes, renewable energy.\nA: Some say there is no alternative.\nB: 'Without alternative' is a dangerous word.",funFact:"[AR] From Latin 'alternare.' 'Eine Alternative finden' (to find an alternative). 'Alternativlos' was Germany's un-word of the year 2010. It means there is no other option."},
        {type:"teach",trg:"die Klimaanlage",src:"[AR] air conditioning",pos:"noun",gender:"f",note:"[AR] Klima + Anlage (system/facility). Rare in German homes.\nMost Germans say: open the window. Fresh air beats everything.",example:"A: Brauchen wir eine Klimaanlage?\nB: Nein, öffne das Fenster.\nA: Bei 40 Grad?\nB: Okay, vielleicht doch eine Klimaanlage.",exampleSrc:"[AR] A: Do we need air conditioning?\nB: No, open the window.\nA: At 40 degrees?\nB: Okay, maybe air conditioning after all.",funFact:"[AR] Klima + Anlage (system/facility). Air conditioning. Rare in German homes. 'Brauchen wir eine Klimaanlage?' is the summer debate. Most Germans say no. Open the window."},
        {type:"teach",trg:"der Hersteller",src:"[AR] manufacturer",pos:"noun",gender:"m",note:"[AR] Her (here/toward) + stellen (to place). The one who places\nsomething into existence. 'Vom Hersteller empfohlen.'",example:"A: Wer ist der Hersteller?\nB: Ein deutscher Hersteller.\nA: Vom Hersteller empfohlen?\nB: Ja, mit Garantie.",exampleSrc:"[AR] A: Who is the manufacturer?\nB: A German manufacturer.\nA: Recommended by the manufacturer?\nB: Yes, with warranty.",funFact:"[AR] Her (here/toward) + stellen (to place). Manufacturer. 'Automobilhersteller' (car manufacturer). 'Vom Hersteller empfohlen' (recommended by the manufacturer). The one who places something into existence."},
        {type:"story",speaker:"verumius",mood:"reflective",art:"de-kreuzberg-street",trg:"Mein Nachbar hat mich gestern gefragt, ob ich bei der Aufräumaktion im Park helfen kann. Nicht weil ich Ausländer bin. Sondern weil ich der bin, der immer den Müll aufsammelt. In Kreuzberg ist das eine Identität.",src:"[AR] My neighbor asked me yesterday if I could help with the cleanup in the park. Not because I am a foreigner. But because I am the one who always picks up the trash. In Kreuzberg, that is an identity."},
        {type:"teach",trg:"die Feuerwehr",src:"[AR] fire department",pos:"noun",gender:"f",note:"[AR] Feuer (fire) + Wehr (defense). Fire defense. Call 112.\nGerman volunteer fire departments have 1 million members.",example:"A: Ruf die Feuerwehr! 112!\nB: Ich rufe sofort an.\nA: Die Feuerwehr kommt schnell.\nB: In fünf Minuten sind sie da.",exampleSrc:"[AR] A: Call the fire department! 112!\nB: I'll call right away.\nA: The fire department comes quickly.\nB: In five minutes they are there.",funFact:"[AR] Feuer (fire) + Wehr (defense). Fire defense = fire department. 'Die Feuerwehr rufen' (to call the fire department). Call 112. German volunteer fire departments have 1 million members. Heroes in every village."},
        {type:"teach",trg:"die Umweltverschmutzung",src:"[AR] environmental pollution",pos:"noun",gender:"f",note:"[AR] Umwelt + Verschmutzung (pollution). 22 letters.\nA compound noun that carries the weight of the problem.",example:"A: Umweltverschmutzung ist ein globales Problem.\nB: Ja, überall auf der Welt.\nA: Wie können wir Umweltverschmutzung reduzieren?\nB: Weniger Abgase, weniger Plastik.",exampleSrc:"[AR] A: Environmental pollution is a global problem.\nB: Yes, everywhere in the world.\nA: How can we reduce environmental pollution?\nB: Fewer emissions, less plastic.",funFact:"[AR] Umwelt + Verschmutzung (pollution). Environmental pollution. 22 letters. A compound noun that carries the weight of the problem. 'Umweltverschmutzung reduzieren' (to reduce environmental pollution)."},
        {type:"teach",trg:"der Zünder",src:"[AR] igniter, detonator",pos:"noun",gender:"m",note:"[AR] From 'zünden' (to ignite). 'Zündstoff' (explosive material,\nalso figuratively: a hot topic). The dating app is named after this concept.",example:"A: Der Zünder funktioniert nicht.\nB: Versuch es nochmal.\nA: Das Thema ist Zündstoff.\nB: Ja, sehr kontrovers.",exampleSrc:"[AR] A: The igniter doesn't work.\nB: Try again.\nA: The topic is explosive material.\nB: Yes, very controversial.",funFact:"[AR] From 'zünden' (to ignite). 'Zündstoff' (explosive material, also figuratively: a hot topic). The dating app Tinder is named after this concept: something that ignites."},
        {type:"teach",trg:"das Zündholz",src:"[AR] match (for lighting)",pos:"noun",gender:"n",note:"[AR] Zünd (ignite) + Holz (wood). Synonym of Streichholz.\nSouthern German prefers Zündholz, northern prefers Streichholz.",example:"A: Hast du ein Zündholz?\nB: Meinst du Streichholz?\nA: Ja, dasselbe. Regional verschieden.\nB: Süddeutsch sagt Zündholz.",exampleSrc:"[AR] A: Do you have a match?\nB: You mean Streichholz?\nA: Yes, the same thing. Regional difference.\nB: Southern German says Zündholz.",funFact:"[AR] Zünd (ignite) + Holz (wood). A match. Synonym of Streichholz. Southern German prefers Zündholz, northern prefers Streichholz. Same object, regional word choice."},
        {type:"teach",trg:"die Form",src:"[AR] form, shape",pos:"noun",gender:"f",note:"[AR] From Latin 'forma.' 'In Form' (in shape/fit).\n'Die Form wahren' (to keep up appearances).",example:"A: In welcher Form ist das Grundstück?\nB: Rechteckig.\nA: Bist du in Form?\nB: Ja, ich trainiere jeden Tag.",exampleSrc:"[AR] A: What shape is the plot of land?\nB: Rectangular.\nA: Are you in shape?\nB: Yes, I train every day.",funFact:"[AR] From Latin 'forma.' 'In Form' (in shape/fit), 'Formular' (form to fill out). 'Die Form wahren' (to keep up appearances). A word that spans fitness, bureaucracy, and etiquette."},
        {type:"teach",trg:"unterstützen",src:"[AR] to support",pos:"verb",gender:null,note:"[AR] Unter (under) + stützen (to prop up). To support from below.\n'Die Regierung unterstützt erneuerbare Energien.'",example:"A: Unterstützt die Regierung Solarenergie?\nB: Ja, mit Förderprogrammen.\nA: Wie kann ich die Umwelt unterstützen?\nB: Weniger verbrauchen und mehr recyceln.",exampleSrc:"[AR] A: Does the government support solar energy?\nB: Yes, with funding programs.\nA: How can I support the environment?\nB: Consume less and recycle more.",funFact:"[AR] Unter (under) + stützen (to prop up). To support from below. 'Erneuerbare Energien unterstützen' (to support renewable energies). Regular verb. Related to Unterstützung (support, the noun)."},
        {type:"teach",trg:"entsorgen",src:"[AR] to dispose of",pos:"verb",gender:null,note:"[AR] Ent- (away from) + sorgen (to care). To dispose of.\nThe ent- prefix removes the care: you send it away.",example:"A: Wie entsorge ich Batterien?\nB: In die grüne Sammelbox.\nA: Und Sondermüll?\nB: Zum Wertstoffhof bringen.",exampleSrc:"[AR] A: How do I dispose of batteries?\nB: In the green collection box.\nA: And hazardous waste?\nB: Take it to the recycling center.",funFact:"[AR] Ent- (away from) + sorgen (to care). To dispose of. 'Müll entsorgen' (to dispose of trash). 'Sondermüll entsorgen' (to dispose of hazardous waste). The ent- prefix removes the care: you send it away."},
        {type:"teach",trg:"schaden",src:"[AR] to damage, to harm",pos:"verb",gender:null,note:"[AR] Takes dative. 'Der Umwelt schaden' (to harm the environment).\n'Rauchen schadet der Gesundheit.' Also a noun: der Schaden.",example:"A: Plastik schadet der Umwelt.\nB: Ja, besonders dem Meer.\nA: Rauchen schadet der Gesundheit.\nB: Das weiß jeder.",exampleSrc:"[AR] A: Plastic harms the environment.\nB: Yes, especially the sea.\nA: Smoking damages health.\nB: Everyone knows that.",funFact:"[AR] 'Der Umwelt schaden' (to harm the environment). Takes dative. 'Rauchen schadet der Gesundheit' (Smoking damages health). Also a noun: der Schaden (the damage)."},
        {type:"teach",trg:"vergrößern",src:"[AR] to enlarge, to increase",pos:"verb",gender:null,note:"[AR] Ver- + groß (big). 'Das Bild vergrößern' (to enlarge the image).\nThe opposite: verkleinern (to make smaller).",example:"A: Kannst du das Bild vergrößern?\nB: Ja, wie groß?\nA: Wir müssen den Abstand vergrößern.\nB: Okay, mehr Platz zwischen uns.",exampleSrc:"[AR] A: Can you enlarge the image?\nB: Yes, how big?\nA: We need to increase the distance.\nB: Okay, more space between us.",funFact:"[AR] Ver- + groß (big). 'Das Bild vergrößern' (to enlarge the image). 'Den Abstand vergrößern' (to increase the distance). The opposite: verkleinern (to make smaller)."},
        {type:"teach",trg:"verbrennen",src:"[AR] to burn (up), to incinerate",pos:"verb",gender:null,note:"[AR] Ver- + brennen. Irregular: verbrannte, verbrannt.\nThe ver- prefix means to completion: burned up entirely.",example:"A: Darf man Müll verbrennen?\nB: Nur in speziellen Anlagen.\nA: Ich habe mich verbrannt!\nB: Kaltes Wasser, schnell!",exampleSrc:"[AR] A: Is it allowed to burn trash?\nB: Only in special facilities.\nA: I burned myself!\nB: Cold water, quick!",funFact:"[AR] Ver- + brennen. Irregular: verbrannte, verbrannt. 'Müll verbrennen' (to incinerate trash). 'Sich verbrennen' (to burn oneself). The ver- prefix means to completion: burned up entirely."},
        {type:"teach",trg:"elektr-",src:"[AR] electr- (prefix for adjectives)",pos:"part",gender:null,note:"[AR] From Greek 'elektron' (amber). 'Elektrisch' (electric),\n'Elektronik' (electronics), 'Elektrizität' (electricity).",example:"A: Ist das elektrisch?\nB: Ja, rein elektrisch.\nA: Elektrische Geräte verbrauchen Strom.\nB: Energieeffiziente Geräte sparen Geld.",exampleSrc:"[AR] A: Is that electric?\nB: Yes, purely electric.\nA: Electrical devices use electricity.\nB: Energy-efficient devices save money.",funFact:"[AR] From Greek 'elektron' (amber). 'Elektrisch' (electric), 'Elektronik' (electronics), 'Elektrizität' (electricity). The elektr- base forms adjectives and abstract nouns about electricity."},
        {type:"teach",trg:"elektro-",src:"[AR] electro- (prefix for compound nouns)",pos:"part",gender:null,note:"[AR] 'Elektroauto' (electric car), 'Elektroherd' (electric stove).\nGermany's Elektromobilität push aims for 15 million e-cars by 2030.",example:"A: Fährst du ein Elektroauto?\nB: Ja, seit einem Jahr.\nA: Und ein Elektroherd?\nB: Ja, Gas ist mir zu gefährlich.",exampleSrc:"[AR] A: Do you drive an electric car?\nB: Yes, for a year.\nA: And an electric stove?\nB: Yes, gas is too dangerous for me.",funFact:"[AR] 'Elektroauto' (electric car), 'Elektroherd' (electric stove), 'Elektrogerät' (electrical device). Germany's Elektromobilität (e-mobility) push aims for 15 million e-cars by 2030."},
        {type:"teach",trg:"öko-",src:"[AR] eco- (prefix)",pos:"part",gender:null,note:"[AR] From Greek 'oikos' (house/household). 'Ökologie' (ecology),\n'Ökostrom' (green electricity). 'Öko' by itself is slang for environmentalist.",example:"A: Kaufst du Ökostrom?\nB: Ja, und Öko-Lebensmittel.\nA: Bist du ein Öko?\nB: Ja, stolz darauf!",exampleSrc:"[AR] A: Do you buy green electricity?\nB: Yes, and organic food.\nA: Are you an eco-person?\nB: Yes, proud of it!",funFact:"[AR] From Greek 'oikos' (house/household). 'Ökologie' (ecology), 'Ökostrom' (green electricity), 'Ökosystem' (ecosystem). The prefix that turns everything green. 'Öko' by itself is slang for an environmentalist."},
        {type:"teach",trg:"über-",src:"[AR] over-/above-/beyond- (prefix)",pos:"part",gender:null,note:"[AR] 'Überdurchschnittlich' (above average), 'überall' (everywhere),\n'übertreiben' (to exaggerate). The most productive German prefix.",example:"A: Das ist überdurchschnittlich gut.\nB: Ja, weit über dem Durchschnitt.\nA: Übertreib nicht!\nB: Ich übertreibe nicht. Es ist überall so.",exampleSrc:"[AR] A: That is above average.\nB: Yes, far above average.\nA: Don't exaggerate!\nB: I'm not exaggerating. It's like that everywhere.",funFact:"[AR] 'Überdurchschnittlich' (above average), 'überall' (everywhere), 'übertreiben' (to exaggerate). The most productive German prefix. It intensifies everything it touches."},
        {type:"story",speaker:"narrator",mood:"reflective",art:"de-park-bench",trg:"Ein Jahr in Berlin. Der verlorene Tourist vom Flughafen ist jetzt ein Berliner, der seinen Müll trennt, sein Fahrrad reparieren lässt und jeden Pfandautomaten in Kreuzberg kennt. Die nächste Stufe wartet: die Prüfung.",src:"[AR] One year in Berlin. The lost tourist from the airport is now a Berliner who separates his trash, has his bike repaired, and knows every deposit machine in Kreuzberg. The next level awaits: the exam."},
        {type:"mc",q:"Umweltverschmutzung, Klimaanlage, Hersteller. Zu welchem Bereich gehören diese Wörter?",opts:["Essen und Kochen","Umwelt und Industrie","Reise und Transport","Gesundheit und Medizin"],ans:"Umwelt und Industrie",hint:"[AR] All three words relate to nature, production, or environmental impacts."},
        {type:"fb",s:"Der {1} Tourist vom Flughafen ist jetzt ein richtiger Berliner.",a:["verlorene"],opts:["verlorene","verloren","verlierender","Verlierer"],hint:"[AR] The tourist WAS lost. Completed action as adjective. Partizip II + adjective ending.",sSrc:"[AR] The lost tourist from the airport is now a real Berliner."},
        {type:"mc",q:"Verumius lässt sein Fahrrad reparieren. Wer macht die eigentliche Reparatur?",opts:[
            "Ein Mechaniker oder Fahrradladen",
            "Mia repariert es für ihn",
            "Verumius repariert es selbst",
            "Niemand, es bleibt kaputt"
          ],ans:"Ein Mechaniker oder Fahrradladen",hint:"[AR] Causative lassen means: someone else performs the action. Verumius organizes it."},
        {type:"story",speaker:"verumius",mood:"grateful",art:"de-park-bench",trg:"Mia, Lukas, Elif. Ohne euch hätte ich das nicht geschafft. Ihr habt mir nicht nur Deutsch beigebracht. Ihr habt mir beigebracht, wie man hier lebt. Und dass man Joghurtbecher ausspült.",src:"[AR] Mia, Lukas, Elif. Without you I would not have managed this. You didn't just teach me German. You taught me how to live here. And that you rinse out yogurt cups."},
        {type:"tip",title:"Deutsche Umweltkultur",text:"[AR] Germany's environmental awareness is deeply rooted.\n\nPfand: bottle deposit. 25 cents for plastic, 8 cents for glass. Return rate: 98%.\nMülltrennung: at least four bins. Neighbors will correct you.\nEnergiewende: the switch to renewable energy. Target: 80% by 2030.\nBio: Bio-Produkte hold large market shares. The Bio-Siegel is trusted.\n\nWhen Mia says 'Du bist ein richtiger Berliner geworden,' she means more than geography. Separating waste, saving energy, returning bottles: these are acts of belonging.",deepDive:{title:"Environmental identity in Germany",text:"[AR] Germany's relationship with nature has deep cultural roots. The Romantic movement (18th-19th century) celebrated forests and landscapes. The Wandervogel youth movement (1896) promoted hiking and outdoor life.\n\nToday, this manifests as:\n- The Green Party (Die Grünen): part of multiple federal governments\n- Pfandsystem: 98% bottle return rate\n- Energiewende: the most ambitious energy transition in the world\n- Organic food market: largest in Europe\n\nFor immigrants, adopting environmental habits becomes a marker of cultural integration. When Mia says Verumius is a 'richtiger Berliner,' his environmental behavior is the proof."}}
      ]}
  ]};

export default UNIT_22_AR;
